Papa

03:22.335 --> 03:24.137
Aye, aye, Pippi!

03:25.605 --> 03:27.641
Why do we want all these
necklaces and stuff?

03:27.708 --> 03:30.544
Gifts for the
Kurrekurre islanders,
of course.

03:30.610 --> 03:34.581
And I suppose these
are to buy me a dress
fit for a queen!

03:34.648 --> 03:38.151
[ Laughing ]
There you're wrong,
me little darlin'.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.754
They're to keep you
out of the pot.

03:40.821 --> 03:45.659
Little girl stew is a delicacy
if they're still cannibals
like the good old days.

03:45.726 --> 03:48.962
Papa... save me!

03:49.029 --> 03:51.698
[ Laughing ]
I'll show you!

03:55.769 --> 03:58.672
<i>Right! Onto Alfonso!</i>

04:00.173 --> 04:01.374
No! Hey!

04:01.441 --> 04:04.277
Are we gonna take Alfonso
ashore, Papa?

04:04.344 --> 04:07.180
Of course.
Aren't I the "Terror
of the South Seas"?

04:07.247 --> 04:12.619
We'll ride ashore in style.
Maybe they'll think
I'm King Neptune.

04:12.686 --> 04:15.856
King Neptune?
Never heard of him.

04:15.922 --> 04:18.658
    It's time you went back
    to school.
Oh!

04:18.725 --> 04:20.527
                Fridolf.
Yes, sir?

04:20.594 --> 04:24.030
Take five
and learn the princess
some history stuff...

04:24.097 --> 04:27.033
that'll come in handy
when she's a boss like me.

04:27.100 --> 04:30.303
Count on me, sir.
All right, Pippi, history.

04:30.370 --> 04:32.973
Take notes.

04:33.039 --> 04:37.811
Okay, Mr. Neilson, if I have
to learn this rotten old
history stuff, so do you.

04:41.348 --> 04:42.415
<i>All right,</i>

04:42.482 --> 04:47.220
in the beginning,
there were... apples,

04:47.287 --> 04:51.725
oranges... and bananas!

04:51.792 --> 04:54.995
[ Together ]
And Mr. Neilson
loves bananas!

04:55.061 --> 04:57.497
[ Chittering ]

