05:09.910 --> 05:13.914
Into the rigging,
and down with the mainsail!

05:13.980 --> 05:18.051
It's plain as Pippi's nose,
there's foul weather ahead!

05:18.118 --> 05:20.020
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>

05:20.086 --> 05:24.858
Sorry, Fridolf, I can't
study anymore. They need me
in the crow's nest.

05:28.995 --> 05:34.301
- [ Blowing Conch Shell,
    Shouting ]
- [ Chittering ]

05:56.223 --> 06:00.126
- Help! Papa!
- What is it, Pippi?

06:00.193 --> 06:03.563
A big wave...
coming towards the ship!

06:03.630 --> 06:06.967
- Come down now!
- No way n!

06:07.033 --> 06:08.468
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Help!</i>

06:16.376 --> 06:20.547
    Take over, Fridolf.
    I've got to get Pippi down.
Aye, aye, Captain.

06:20.614 --> 06:22.482
Papa, I'm scared!

06:25.852 --> 06:29.389
Lash yourself
to the mast, girl!

06:29.456 --> 06:32.659
I'm comin' up for ya!

06:32.726 --> 06:35.495
[ Papa ]
Hang on!

06:37.597 --> 06:39.599
Papa, I'm slipping!

06:39.666 --> 06:44.638
Hang on!
If I lose you,
remember the Villa Villekulla.

06:44.704 --> 06:47.007
<i>The Gulf Stream</i>
<i>will take you there.</i>

06:51.111 --> 06:54.381
We'll come out on top
like we always do.

06:56.616 --> 06:58.084
[ Screaming ]

07:01.254 --> 07:03.890
Help!
[ Screams ]

07:05.225 --> 07:08.628
Papa!
 Papa, where are you?

07:10.964 --> 07:16.369
I'm drifting away
toward the island.
The current's taking me.

07:18.171 --> 07:20.807
Papa, it's taking me
the other way.

07:23.643 --> 07:24.844
<i>[ Papa ]</i>
<i>Grab hold of the raft.</i>

07:26.446 --> 07:29.516
Make for
the Villa Villekulla.

07:34.688 --> 07:37.490
Papa! Papa!

07:37.557 --> 07:41.161
<i>[ Papa's Voice ]</i>
<i>I'll find you somehow.</i>
<i>I love ya, Pippi.</i>

07:53.373 --> 07:55.608
I wish some kids
lived there.

07:55.675 --> 07:59.145
It would be fun
to have best friends
living right next door.

08:05.685 --> 08:07.854
Hello.
You kids live here?

08:07.921 --> 08:12.292
No. We live in that house
over there.
        The nice white one.

08:12.359 --> 08:17.263
Well, who lives in this dump?
    Nobody. It's been empty
    practically forever.

08:17.330 --> 08:20.567
What did I tell ya?
Absentee ownership.
Probably dead.

08:20.633 --> 08:23.069
We'll pull it down
and the whole plot'll develop.

08:23.136 --> 08:26.439
You can't do that!
We play in that tree
over there sometimes.

08:26.506 --> 08:31.211
Not anymore you don't!
Come on. Take pictures of it.
Lot of pictures.

08:31.277 --> 08:35.849
I'll knock it down, and we pour
cement as far as you can see.
Everything living gets cut down.

08:35.914 --> 08:38.618
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>It's another gold mine, boss!</i>

08:40.520 --> 08:44.256
We're drifting
in the right direction,
and we're not gonna starve.

08:44.324 --> 08:46.659
[ Chitters ]

08:46.726 --> 08:48.294
Keep reeling 'em in,
Mr. Neilson.

08:53.566 --> 08:57.137
Mr. Neilson and I
are very grateful to you
for saving us.

08:57.203 --> 09:00.407
[ Yawns ]
    But you've got to eat.

09:00.473 --> 09:03.743
[ Mumbling ]
        That's all there is!

09:09.315 --> 09:10.283
Mmm, not bad.

09:10.350 --> 09:14.454
- Blahhh!
- [ Burps, Laughs ]

09:17.323 --> 09:19.826
Well done, Mr. Neilson.

09:19.893 --> 09:24.364
You might not be the prettiest
monkey at sea, but you're
the cleverest and thdearest.

09:24.431 --> 09:29.035
- What about me?
- Okay, okay,
  I love you too.

09:29.102 --> 09:33.173
And now we must stick together,
like the time
when we were in Timbuktu.

09:33.239 --> 09:37.544
So when Papa
finds his way back,
he'll say, "Well done, guys."

09:37.610 --> 09:39.879
<i>[ Mr. Neilson Chittering ]</i>

09:39.946 --> 09:43.583
Wake up, Mr. Neilson.
Another lovely day.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.718
I hope Papa made it.

09:47.754 --> 09:53.927
Don't worry, Alfonso,
the Gulf Stream will take us
home, just like Papa said.

09:53.993 --> 09:57.630
<i>[ Boy ] But, Dad,</i>
<i>why would anyone wanna</i>
<i>tear down Villa Villekulla?</i>

09:57.697 --> 10:01.000
Progress, Tommy.
Mr. Blackhart has plans...

10:01.067 --> 10:06.372
to build all sorts of houses
and a golf course
and a swimming pool.

10:06.439 --> 10:09.542
    Sounds nice.
    Maybe we should move.
[ Children ] No!

10:09.609 --> 10:11.978
            I don't wanna move!
And what about
our tree?

10:12.045 --> 10:14.380
Aah. There's plenty
of other trees, Tommy.

10:14.447 --> 10:16.483
You and I'll go out
and find another one together.

10:16.549 --> 10:19.652
Besides, this town
could use some changes.

10:19.719 --> 10:23.223
Now, it's getting late.
[ Children Groan ]
Oh, come on.

10:23.289 --> 10:26.259
Time to bed.
Come on. Off you go.
    Couple more minutes?

10:26.326 --> 10:30.497
                Five minutes.
Nope, lights out
in half an hour.

10:30.563 --> 10:33.299
           How 'bout an hour?
<i>No. Sorry.</i>

10:33.366 --> 10:35.568
Time for bed.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.704
Time for bed.

10:37.770 --> 10:39.939
Now, you know where we are
if you need us, right?

10:40.006 --> 10:42.242
Yes, good night.

10:42.308 --> 10:45.111
You'll be all right?
                Yeah.

10:45.178 --> 10:47.580
        Love you.
[ Children ] Love you.

10:54.721 --> 10:57.257
Mom says the Villa
is over a hundred years old.

10:57.323 --> 11:01.528
         <i>They can't tear it down</i>
         <i>just like that.</i>
Just won't be the same anymore.

11:01.594 --> 11:04.731
<i>I don't wanna leave here...</i>
<i>ever.</i>

11:04.797 --> 11:10.170
<i>[ Tommy ] You know, Annika,</i>
<i>there's something strange</i>
<i>going on in there.</i>

11:10.236 --> 11:12.839
<i>[ Annika ]</i>
<i>You mean somebody's</i>
<i>in there?</i>

11:12.906 --> 11:17.410
Or maybe even... ghosts?

11:17.477 --> 11:21.014
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>Yeah! Could be even a ghost.</i>
<i>Let's go check it out.</i>

11:22.849 --> 11:25.385
See anything?
    No.

11:27.687 --> 11:30.990
Besides,
you can't see ghosts.

11:32.792 --> 11:36.863
Well,
if you can't see ghosts,
         <i>[ Door Slams ]</i>

11:36.930 --> 11:39.933
        then what
        are we looking for?
Shh!

11:49.042 --> 11:51.377
<i>[ Creaking Noise ]</i>
               What was that?

11:51.444 --> 11:55.248
The step creaked.
        Don't follow so close.

11:59.419 --> 12:01.287
[ Screaming ]

12:05.558 --> 12:07.794
[ Tommy ] Look.
It's up there.

12:07.860 --> 12:09.929
If I say run, run!

12:09.996 --> 12:12.932
Okay. Where?

12:12.999 --> 12:15.001
Just run.

12:15.068 --> 12:18.905
Look. Do ghosts
have big shoes?

12:18.972 --> 12:21.040
Give me the bat.

12:21.107 --> 12:25.645
Can you hit a ghost?
            Shh. Stop asking
            so many questions.

12:27.647 --> 12:29.515
You see?
It's nothing.

12:29.582 --> 12:32.318
Probably just--

12:32.385 --> 12:35.021
- [ Whinnies ]
- [ Screaming ]

12:36.889 --> 12:39.692
[ Screaming ]

12:39.759 --> 12:42.895
[ Mr. Neilson Screeching ]

12:42.962 --> 12:47.233
           [ Screaming ]
<i>[ Screeching ]</i>

13:01.748 --> 13:03.616
Hi.
Who are you?

13:03.683 --> 13:06.152
       You're not a ghost?
<i>'Course not.</i>

13:06.219 --> 13:09.522
The ghosts live up in the attic.
     <i>[ Tommy ]</i>
     <i>We know. We just saw one.</i>

13:09.589 --> 13:14.494
It was big and white
and had spots all over it.

13:14.560 --> 13:16.996
<i>That's my horse, Alfonso.</i>

13:17.063 --> 13:19.766
What's a horse doing
in the attic?

13:19.832 --> 13:24.037
Beats me. I keep telling him
not to go up there,
but he doesn't listen.

13:26.306 --> 13:29.375
Alfonso,
get down on the porch,
where you belong.

13:29.442 --> 13:31.644
[ Whinnying ]
No way!

13:31.711 --> 13:34.247
You see?
He won't listen.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.883
My name's Pippi.
Pippi Longstocking.

13:36.949 --> 13:40.420
I'm Tommy, and this
is my sister Annika.
What are you doing here?

13:40.486 --> 13:44.557
I live here, of course.
    Are you gonna stay here
    all by yourself?

13:44.624 --> 13:49.228
I'm not all by myself.
Mr. Neilson and Alfonso
live with me too.

13:49.295 --> 13:52.332
[ Chittering ]
     <i>[ Annika ] Oh, is</i>
     <i>Mr. Neilson your father?</i>

13:52.398 --> 13:56.002
    This is Mr. Neilson.
[ Chittering ]

13:59.872 --> 14:03.142
My father is a sea captain
who was washed overboard
in a storm.

14:03.209 --> 14:05.378
        Did he drown?
Of course not.

14:05.445 --> 14:08.915
He lives
on the Kurrekurre Island.
He's the king of the cannibals.

14:08.981 --> 14:12.352
Cannibals?
Real cannibals?

14:12.418 --> 14:15.421
       There's no such thing
       today.
<i>[ Pippi ] How do you know?</i>

14:15.488 --> 14:18.558
You've never been there,
have you?

14:18.624 --> 14:21.027
And do they really...
eat you?

14:21.094 --> 14:23.463
Yeah.

14:23.529 --> 14:26.666
Which reminds me.
I'm hungry.
You guys hungry?

14:26.733 --> 14:28.534
           We're always hungry.
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Great.</i>

14:35.174 --> 14:39.812
<i>[ Children Singing,</i>
<i>  Laughing ]</i>

14:39.879 --> 14:42.648
What the heck's that ruckus
over there?

14:42.715 --> 14:45.885
What could it be?

14:45.952 --> 14:49.288
        You don't suppose
        Tommy and Annika--
No, I'll go see.

14:49.355 --> 14:54.160
[ Singing, Laughing ]

14:54.227 --> 14:56.896
Hey, Pippi!

14:56.963 --> 14:58.898
Hey, Annika!

15:01.134 --> 15:03.236
<i>Pancakes, Alfonso?</i>

15:03.302 --> 15:05.405
[ Singing ]

15:05.471 --> 15:07.974
[ Whinnying ]
Pancakes.
Something new.

15:08.040 --> 15:10.209
[ Continue Singing ]

15:14.080 --> 15:16.215
<i>[ Laughter ]</i>

15:20.753 --> 15:22.855
<i>Tommy!</i>
<i>Annika!</i>

15:22.922 --> 15:25.458
Just what in blazes
do you think you're doing?

15:25.525 --> 15:27.794
We're just having
a midnight snack.

15:27.860 --> 15:33.065
 <i>Care to join us?</i>
I have never seen
such a mess in my entire life!

15:35.168 --> 15:39.772
You two are going to march
right home this very instant...

15:39.839 --> 15:42.074
and go to bed!

15:42.141 --> 15:46.312
And as for you, I don't know
who you think you are or what
you think you're doing here,

15:46.379 --> 15:49.315
but I'm going to get
to the bottom of this
first thing in the morning.

15:49.382 --> 15:51.684
March!

15:51.751 --> 15:53.753
[ Chittering ]

15:55.054 --> 15:56.956
Nice meeting you.

15:57.023 --> 15:58.424
Aah!

16:00.226 --> 16:02.395
[ Chittering ]

16:05.331 --> 16:08.367
Thank goodness
I only have you and Alfonso
to worry about.

16:08.434 --> 16:10.503
Alfonso?

16:10.570 --> 16:13.973
[ Tommy ] Her name
is Pippi Longstocking.
    And she's come to live here.

16:14.040 --> 16:17.743
I don't know what got
into you two. How could you
do something like this?

16:22.548 --> 16:24.517
Here, darling.

16:24.584 --> 16:27.487
Oh, thank you.
I'm-I'm so confused.

16:27.553 --> 16:30.656
That house stands empty
for heaven knows how many years.

16:30.723 --> 16:34.327
Suddenly in
the middle of the night, some
11-year-old terror moves in.

16:34.393 --> 16:36.762
I know.
Our kids seem
to love it.

16:36.829 --> 16:39.031
You should've seen them.
Uh, uh, a flying horse.

16:39.098 --> 16:41.601
<i>How do we even know that</i>
<i>it's her father's house?</i>

16:41.667 --> 16:44.303
<i>You can be sure</i>
<i>I'm going to get</i>
<i>to the bottom of this.</i>

16:44.370 --> 16:47.974
<i>[ Alfonso ] I'm tired.</i>
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Keep your head still, Alfonso.</i>

16:49.809 --> 16:52.545
Hi. We're running
a little late this morning.

16:52.612 --> 16:56.916
Oh, those are for you,
Annika and Tommy.
         <i>Thanks. A real sword.</i>

16:58.851 --> 17:01.187
Did you wash
behind your ears?
            [ Mumbles ]

17:01.254 --> 17:04.323
You can't expect a horse
to do for himself.

17:04.390 --> 17:07.159
Shh. He thinks
he's just like us.

17:07.226 --> 17:09.561
Okay, you can go out
and play now.

17:09.628 --> 17:13.833
<i>But don't tease Mr. Neilson,</i>
<i>or you'll have to come</i>
<i>right back in.</i>

17:13.900 --> 17:15.334
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Next on the list.</i>

17:20.940 --> 17:23.108
<i>Ahh, nothing</i>
<i>like a morning bath.</i>

17:23.175 --> 17:26.112
But, Pippi, you've got
all your clothes on!

17:26.178 --> 17:28.347
That's because
it's laundry day.

17:31.617 --> 17:34.353
Well, that's enough of that.
There is such a thing
as being too clean.

17:37.256 --> 17:40.560
<i>You'll catch your death of cold</i>
<i>if you stand around like that.</i>

17:40.626 --> 17:42.895
Since when do people die
from being wet?

17:42.962 --> 17:46.499
That's what my mom
always says.

17:46.566 --> 17:48.601
Well, now that
you mention it,

17:48.668 --> 17:52.772
I do remember one time
at the North Pole
when I was so frozen...

17:52.838 --> 17:57.243
after swimming with some seals
and some Eskimo kids that I had
to dry myself off like this.

18:15.728 --> 18:17.163
See?

18:17.229 --> 18:21.167
That was easy.
Now we're ready for a game.

18:21.233 --> 18:25.338
Game of what?
Rub-a-dub-dub scrubbing day.
It's my favorite day.

18:25.404 --> 18:28.374
Everything's soapy,
so we might as well
scrub the floor.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.409
Scrub the floor?

18:30.476 --> 18:33.012
<i>That's not a game.</i>
           You wanna bet?

18:34.347 --> 18:37.450
<i>Oh, Pippi, what a mess!</i>

18:37.516 --> 18:39.352
Here, put these on
and follow me.

18:46.726 --> 18:48.928
[ Pippi And Chorus ]
 I put my
  scrubbing shoes on

18:48.995 --> 18:52.832
And I never get the blues
 on Monday morning

18:52.898 --> 18:54.834
Yeah, yeah

18:54.900 --> 18:57.303
This dust'll be a goner

18:57.370 --> 19:01.340
As I hit each dirty corner
 without warning

19:01.407 --> 19:03.609
Yeah, yeah

19:03.676 --> 19:07.580
Throwing soapsuds everywhere
 We're being careful
 very careful

19:07.647 --> 19:12.118
To enjoy ourselves
 each step of the way

19:12.184 --> 19:15.855
Scrubbing day
 is a holiday

19:15.921 --> 19:20.426
And the game we play
 is as wild as it can get

19:20.493 --> 19:24.063
Scrubbing day
 is my favorite day

19:24.130 --> 19:27.967
'Cause on scrubbing day
 we make everything get wet

19:36.142 --> 19:41.447
The greater the confusion
 I have come to the conclusion
 things get cleaner

19:41.514 --> 19:43.983
Oh, yeah

19:44.050 --> 19:47.253
The white is whiter
 Red is redder
 Blue is bluer

19:47.319 --> 19:49.388
And the green
 gets greener

19:49.455 --> 19:51.724
Yeah, yeah

19:51.791 --> 19:55.728
Throwing water everywhere
 There is a feeling
 in the air

19:55.795 --> 20:00.066
That any minute
 we could all float away

20:00.132 --> 20:04.103
Everybody
 Scrubbing day
 is a holiday

20:04.170 --> 20:08.641
And the game we play
 is as wild as it can get

20:08.708 --> 20:11.844
Scrubbing day
 is my favorite day

20:11.911 --> 20:15.881
'Cause on scrubbing day
 we make everything get wet

20:20.653 --> 20:23.255
Whoa! It was lucky
I was here to catch you!

20:26.625 --> 20:28.561
<i>[ Mother ]</i>
<i>What a great way</i>
<i>to clean up.</i>

20:28.627 --> 20:30.763
I must try it someday.

20:30.830 --> 20:33.199
This is my mom, Pippi.

20:33.265 --> 20:38.037
Nice mom. My mom is--
She's not here right now.
She's, uh--

20:38.104 --> 20:40.973
<i>I don't mean to be rude, Pippi,</i>
<i>but we're terribly late.</i>

20:41.040 --> 20:43.375
<i>They've got to go</i>
<i>to the dentist.</i>

20:43.442 --> 20:46.245
           Bye, Pippi.
<i>Bye, Pippi.</i>

20:50.116 --> 20:53.119
<i>Wait! Here. Take these.</i>

20:53.185 --> 20:56.355
My father got them
off of an old sailor
who didn't need them anymore.

20:56.422 --> 21:00.459
I don't think
we can use them just now.
But do come and visit.

21:00.526 --> 21:02.495
 <i>That'll be fun.</i>
Bye, Pippi.
                Bye, Pippi.

21:02.561 --> 21:06.298
And when was
your last checkup?

21:09.735 --> 21:10.770
Get back!

21:10.836 --> 21:12.772
<i>Watch your step, boss.</i>

21:14.673 --> 21:16.509
Briefcase.

21:19.712 --> 21:21.480
<i>Good morning!</i>

21:23.582 --> 21:25.551
Nice of you to call.

21:27.052 --> 21:30.656
I'm Pippilotta Delicatessa
Windowshade Longstocking,

21:30.723 --> 21:33.058
daughter of
Captain Efraim Longstocking.

21:33.125 --> 21:36.996
            Pippi for short.
Pippi.
Good morning.

21:37.062 --> 21:40.733
What can I do for you?
Selling vacuums?
I'll take a dozen.

21:40.800 --> 21:45.371
                Wrap them up.
No, I'm not selling.
I'm buying. Oh, this is me.

21:45.437 --> 21:49.441
Dan Blackhart.
Blackhart's Ideal Homes.
If you need it, we've got it.

21:49.508 --> 21:54.180
Well, to be very honest
with you, I don't think
I need anything this morning.

21:54.246 --> 21:56.482
[ Laughing ]
            But,

21:58.818 --> 22:01.921
you can have this wonderfully
spectacular sewing machine
for a dollar.

22:01.987 --> 22:04.390
I don't want your filthy
sewing machine.

22:04.456 --> 22:06.859
I would like to look inside.

22:14.200 --> 22:16.435
Will there be
anything else?

22:16.502 --> 22:20.005
Oh! I wonder
if you'd be interested
in selling this house?

22:20.072 --> 22:21.941
My home?
Selling?

22:22.007 --> 22:23.943
[ Laughing ]

22:24.009 --> 22:25.945
How can you sell a home?

22:27.646 --> 22:29.748
You can't wrap it up.

22:29.815 --> 22:31.817
You can't carry it away.

22:31.884 --> 22:34.787
And you certainly can't
fit it in your car.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.989
Obviously you can't
make much of a living...

22:37.056 --> 22:41.594
if you're trying
to buy houses
other people are living in.

22:41.660 --> 22:45.264
Here's a gold coin
for your troubles.
        Where did you get that?

22:45.331 --> 22:48.267
No big deal.
I have a whole mess of them
down in the basement.

22:48.334 --> 22:52.538
I just help myself
whenever I need to.
        How did they get there?

22:52.605 --> 22:57.376
It's a long story.
But I can tell you this much.

22:57.443 --> 23:01.947
It's part of the treasure
from King Solomon's mines.

23:02.014 --> 23:06.085
I'm afraid
you'll have to go now.
It's Friday. Wash day.

23:06.151 --> 23:07.786
[ Yelling ]

23:09.421 --> 23:11.557
I'm sure
you'll understand.

23:14.393 --> 23:16.228
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

23:16.295 --> 23:17.963
[ Laughing ]

23:18.030 --> 23:22.368
Who is that girl?
What is she doing on a horse?

23:22.434 --> 23:27.039
[ Pippi And Chorus ]
 Watch out, world
  'cause here she comes

23:27.106 --> 23:31.210
<i>And she's bound to teach you</i>
<i> more than one thing </i>

23:31.277 --> 23:36.148
Pippi Longstocking is coming
 into your town

23:36.215 --> 23:39.451
      What is going on here?
<i>The one</i>
<i> no one can keep down </i>

23:39.518 --> 23:42.821
No, no, no, no

23:42.888 --> 23:46.825
Get them in the bus.
Get in there.
In the bus.

23:46.892 --> 23:48.961
Get in the bus. Get
in the bus. Get in the bus.

23:49.028 --> 23:52.831
That's no way to treat kids.
Is that where you go to school?

23:52.898 --> 23:57.236
No. That's the home for
children who have no parents.
Nobody wants them.

23:57.303 --> 24:00.773
Well, all kids
should be wanted and loved.

24:00.839 --> 24:03.976
Maybe their moms and dads
just lost them.

24:05.344 --> 24:07.313
Whoa, whoa

24:07.379 --> 24:13.285
Pippi Longstocking is coming
 into your world

24:13.352 --> 24:16.622
A freckled-faced
 red-haired girl

24:16.689 --> 24:22.027
<i>You ought to know</i>
<i>she'll throw your life</i>
<i>into a whirl </i>

24:27.599 --> 24:29.301
Everybody out.

24:29.368 --> 24:32.104
Unhitch the horse,
my man.

24:32.171 --> 24:36.175
    What are we going
    to buy today, Pippi?
A grand piano.

24:36.241 --> 24:39.878
They don't sell pianos
in there.
            They might today.

24:39.945 --> 24:43.682
Can you play the piano?
            How do I know
            until I've tried?

24:43.749 --> 24:48.554
To play the piano
without a piano takes a lot
of practice, I can tell you.

24:48.620 --> 24:50.789
But how are we gonna pay?

24:53.726 --> 24:56.829
Spanish gold.
Pirates' money.

24:58.530 --> 25:03.135
Pippi says you can find
your own way home.
                [ Nickers ]

25:03.202 --> 25:07.006
            Do you want to go
            with him?
No, not me. Uh-uh, no way.

25:07.072 --> 25:10.342
[ Chattering ]

25:10.409 --> 25:14.113
He really is going home.

25:14.179 --> 25:16.348
They missed
a good sale there.

25:17.950 --> 25:20.719
Hi, freckle-face.
Don't you just love
freckles?

25:20.786 --> 25:23.422
Not much!
            Well, I do.

25:23.489 --> 25:25.758
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>What's going on over there?</i>

25:25.824 --> 25:29.695
Children's home kids.
Come for their haircut
and teeth pulling.

25:29.762 --> 25:32.498
Don't they ever have any fun
when they come to town?

25:32.564 --> 25:35.567
Let's go play with them.

25:35.634 --> 25:37.569
What's wrong?

25:37.636 --> 25:40.773
Orphans.
            Dad says
            we shouldn't.

25:40.839 --> 25:43.876
Why not?
They're just kids like us.
Let's go.

25:43.942 --> 25:48.247
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Quick, quick, quick.</i>
<i>Come along.</i>

25:50.282 --> 25:54.286
        Next two, please.
Come on. You two next.

25:54.353 --> 25:56.955
Hi! What flavor ice cream
do you like best?

25:57.022 --> 25:59.792
[ Shouting ]
Chocolate! Vanilla!

25:59.858 --> 26:01.360
Shh!

26:01.427 --> 26:04.563
Back off!
It's against the rules.

26:04.630 --> 26:09.601
Listen, I want you to go
to the ice cream truck
and get lots of ice cream...

26:09.668 --> 26:11.770
and every kind of candy
that they have.

26:11.837 --> 26:16.408
    Here's some gold coins.
    Okay. Now, go.
Come on, Annika.

26:16.475 --> 26:18.544
You won't get away
with this.

26:18.610 --> 26:21.046
I'm telling Miss Bannister,
and she'll soon
settle your hash.

26:21.113 --> 26:23.916
Miss Bannister?

26:23.982 --> 26:26.118
That settles it.
Now we're gonna have a ball.

26:30.322 --> 26:33.058
<i>[ Girl ]</i>
<i>Miss Bannister?</i>
<i>There's this girl.</i>

26:33.125 --> 26:37.563
She's creating havoc.
There's this girl. She--
She went up there.

26:37.629 --> 26:42.601
I don't see anyone.
You silly, stupid girl.

26:42.668 --> 26:45.604
Now, you mean you want
64 ice cream cones?

26:45.671 --> 26:47.906
And Nestle's Crunch.
 And bubble gum.

26:47.973 --> 26:51.977
And can we have
265 Oh Henry! bars?

26:53.812 --> 26:58.383
[ Laughing ]
You just help yourselves.
It's all yours!

27:01.053 --> 27:04.923
<i>Come on, kids!</i>
<i>It's Pippi Longstocking Day!</i>

27:04.990 --> 27:07.993
[ Drumbeats,
    Accordion ]

27:29.515 --> 27:32.551
The ice cream!
Let's get the ice cream.

27:35.053 --> 27:38.490
That's really something, eh?
Those poor kids
never had such a treat.

27:43.228 --> 27:46.498
[ Man ]
Here comes the ice cream.

27:50.102 --> 27:52.905
Come on, kids!
 Come and get it!

27:52.971 --> 27:55.340
[ Excited Shouting ]

27:57.075 --> 28:00.512
Free ice cream!

28:00.579 --> 28:03.482
[ Excited Shouting ]

28:12.658 --> 28:18.096
There's always been a lot
of talk about Villa Villekulla
being an old pirate hangout.

28:18.163 --> 28:21.266
   But I--
<i>[ Children Shouting ]</i>

28:21.333 --> 28:25.103
I never heard anything
about a buried treasure inside.

28:25.170 --> 28:30.309
There must be records.
Deeds? A bill of sale?
Anything!

28:30.375 --> 28:32.444
Look, I want that place.

28:32.511 --> 28:36.548
And I'm willing to pay
any legal costs to get it,
if you know what I mean.

28:36.615 --> 28:39.318
[ Shouting ]

28:42.688 --> 28:47.593
- Ohhh!
- [ Laughing ] Tommy,
  throw some more. Hurry!

28:47.659 --> 28:52.598
    [ Gasps ]
    Well, go and get 'em!
Yes, Miss Bannister.

29:05.377 --> 29:07.379
Tommy!

29:07.446 --> 29:10.782
I think 've done
enough shopping for today.
I'll be right back.

29:15.454 --> 29:17.489
<i>[ Child ]</i>
<i>Hey, get some more pistachio,</i>
<i>strawberry!</i>

29:17.556 --> 29:19.524
Keep your eyes peeled.

29:20.792 --> 29:24.496
Annika! Tom--

29:24.563 --> 29:28.233
You... dirty rat!

29:28.300 --> 29:32.204
- Okay, Mr. Neilson,
  time to do your stuff.
- Here we go. Here we go.

29:42.014 --> 29:45.684
        [ Whistle Blows ]
You do something!
Arrest somebody!

29:45.751 --> 29:48.787
Yes, ma'am.
[ Whistle Blows ]

29:50.322 --> 29:52.457
Annika!

29:52.524 --> 29:55.894
Tommy!
Eh, watch it!
Tommy!

29:55.961 --> 29:59.197
Would you get out
of my-- Get--

29:59.264 --> 30:01.733
<i>Tommy!</i>

30:06.872 --> 30:09.374
[ Mr. Neilson
  Chittering ]

30:11.610 --> 30:15.314
        All aboard!
Come on, Annika.

30:16.648 --> 30:19.184
Go! Come on!

30:21.586 --> 30:24.523
[ Car Horn Honking ]

30:28.360 --> 30:31.697
- <i>Tommy, Annika,</i>
 <i>come down this minute!</i>
- Hold on!

30:31.763 --> 30:33.832
No, no! Stay up!

30:33.899 --> 30:37.269
- Bye, Dad!
  See you at dinner!
- You'll pay for this!

30:39.338 --> 30:41.673
I know who's responsible
for this!

30:47.346 --> 30:53.118
<i>[ Chorus ]</i>
<i> Pippi Longstocking is coming</i>
<i>  into your town </i>

30:53.185 --> 30:55.120
<i>The one no one--</i>

30:55.187 --> 30:58.290
Riding on a motorcycle!
Flying through the air!

30:58.357 --> 31:00.959
I don't know what
I would have done
if they had crashed.

31:01.026 --> 31:04.796
Honey, Pippi
got them home safely
as she always does.

31:04.863 --> 31:06.932
That's what's important.

31:06.998 --> 31:11.370
I've got a feeling Pippi
would never put
those kids' lives in danger.

31:11.436 --> 31:14.940
Do you know,
she told me...

31:15.006 --> 31:20.278
that she used to ride
with her father on the
Wall of Death in Bangkok?

31:20.345 --> 31:22.414
And you believe that?

31:22.481 --> 31:25.984
That Pippi is
the biggest darned liar
that I have ever seen.

31:26.051 --> 31:28.053
And I'll tell you what.
There's going to be trouble.

31:28.120 --> 31:32.257
That Miss Bannister is
on the warpath. She's gonna
have her way with Pippi yet.

31:32.324 --> 31:34.326
What a shame.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.728
[ Annika ]
Whee!

31:36.795 --> 31:39.831
<i>[ Annika ] Have you</i>
<i>seen the splunk yet?</i>
<i>I don't want him to get me.</i>

31:39.898 --> 31:42.367
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>I'll protect you</i>
<i>if it does.</i>

31:42.434 --> 31:44.536
Be careful,
and don't touch the floor.

31:44.603 --> 31:46.605
<i>The splunk will get you.</i>

31:46.671 --> 31:50.175
And when he does,
he'll tear your legs off...

31:50.242 --> 31:53.011
and stick 'em in your ears.

31:53.078 --> 31:56.615
Do you know,
since Pippi has arrived,

31:56.681 --> 32:00.051
I've never seen
Tommy and Annika so happy.

32:00.118 --> 32:03.455
I never even
see them anymore.

32:03.522 --> 32:06.425
I just miss our happy,
little family dinners.

32:06.491 --> 32:08.427
Look at you.

32:08.493 --> 32:10.829
[ Alfonso Groans ]

32:10.896 --> 32:13.765
Come on!
Then let me go first.
        I can't.

32:13.832 --> 32:15.133
Don't touch the floor.

32:18.670 --> 32:21.006
Come on!
 <i>[ Pippi ]</i>
 <i>Get onto the couch!</i>

32:21.072 --> 32:22.941
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>Now you've got to get</i>
<i>onto the couch, Annika.</i>

32:24.776 --> 32:27.312
<i>Come on!</i>

32:27.379 --> 32:29.047
I did it!

32:29.114 --> 32:31.450
[ All Laughing,
  Shouting ]

32:38.690 --> 32:40.692
What are you kids doing?

32:40.759 --> 32:44.763
Watch out, Mom.
There's a splunk
on the loose!

32:44.830 --> 32:46.932
I got it!
Get out while the going's good.

32:46.998 --> 32:51.703
Well, come along before
your father sees this mess.

32:51.770 --> 32:53.939
<i>[ Annika ]</i>
<i>We've been having fun, Mom.</i>

32:54.005 --> 32:56.408
Pippi, would you like
to come to dinner?

32:56.475 --> 33:00.712
No, thanks, Mrs. "S."
I promised this fabulous swami
in Chittagong...

33:00.779 --> 33:02.914
that I'd never eat out
on Tuesdays,

33:02.981 --> 33:07.752
and there's nothing worse
than lying to a swami.

33:07.819 --> 33:09.588
Bye-bye.
            Bye, Pippi.

33:10.956 --> 33:12.858
Bye!

33:19.064 --> 33:21.566
Let me give you a hand,
ma'am.

33:29.307 --> 33:35.547
<i>[ Alfonso Whinnies ]</i>
<i>Oh, no.</i>

33:35.614 --> 33:40.352
         <i>What are you doing</i>
         <i>up there?</i>
Looking out for a storm.

33:40.418 --> 33:42.721
Well, come down
at once, please.

33:42.787 --> 33:46.191
Why? Do you have
a new game for us to play?

33:46.258 --> 33:48.360
<i>I'm afraid this will be</i>
<i>no game.</i>

33:48.426 --> 33:52.063
I am the welfare worker
from the county.

33:52.130 --> 33:55.433
And there is a place for you
in our children's home.

33:55.500 --> 33:59.304
 <i>I have come to take you there.</i>
But I already have a place
in a children's home.

33:59.371 --> 34:02.073
               Where?
<i>Well, look.</i>

34:02.140 --> 34:06.111
I am a child, and
this is my home. Therefore
I live in a children's home.

34:06.177 --> 34:09.047
<i>And a very comfortable one</i>
<i>at that.</i>

34:09.114 --> 34:11.815
But no child can live alone.

34:11.882 --> 34:13.451
<i>No, no, no.</i>
<i>It's unheard of.</i>

34:13.518 --> 34:18.089
Every child needs
adult supervision
and has to go to school.

34:18.156 --> 34:21.226
        [ Alfonso Laughs ]
        School!
Why?

34:21.293 --> 34:24.896
                To learn things,
                of course.
What kinds of things?

34:26.864 --> 34:29.734
Reading, writing,
arithmetic, history,
geography,

34:29.801 --> 34:32.137
all those things
that a person has to know.

34:32.203 --> 34:34.205
Well,

34:34.272 --> 34:37.641
Fridolf taught me how to count,
enough to count my gold.

34:37.708 --> 34:41.679
<i>And as for the other stuff,</i>
<i>I've gotten along fine</i>
<i>without it for ten years.</i>

34:41.746 --> 34:45.283
So, I'm afraid you'll have
to find children...

34:45.350 --> 34:48.652
for your children's home
someplace else.

34:48.719 --> 34:54.159
Well, if you would just
take ahold of that beast,

34:54.225 --> 34:56.895
I want to see
what's going on inside.

34:56.962 --> 34:59.064
Sure.

34:59.130 --> 35:02.200
But if I were you,
I'd wait and come back
on Friday,

35:02.267 --> 35:05.670
'cause today's splunk day
and they're
all over the place.

35:11.509 --> 35:14.613
       I tried to warn her...
       sort of.
<i>[ Crashing ]</i>

35:17.682 --> 35:19.918
That was a trap
to catch a splunk.

35:19.985 --> 35:23.388
They're such a pain,
always trying to steal my gold.
        Get away! Bug off!

35:23.455 --> 35:26.591
If I let them stay,
they'd eat me out of house
and home.

35:26.658 --> 35:30.962
And that wouldn't do,
'cause then I'd have to go
to the children's home with you.

35:32.697 --> 35:35.000
Don't, don't, don't, don't!

35:35.066 --> 35:40.572
I don't know how to thank you
and those kind people in the
town for thinking so much of me.

35:40.639 --> 35:44.442
But take this and give
those poor children in
the home a nice holiday...

35:44.509 --> 35:46.745
with lots of ice cream
and marshmallows.

35:48.413 --> 35:50.315
[ Laughing ]

35:50.382 --> 35:52.751
[ Chittering ]

35:52.817 --> 35:56.154
Oh, give it here!
Wretch!
        Hey!

35:56.221 --> 35:58.923
She took my hat!
 She took my hat!

35:58.990 --> 36:03.828
Okay, okay, I'll tell you what.
Maybe I'll visit
Tommy and Annika's school.

36:03.895 --> 36:07.432
Who knows?
Might even be fun.
I love drawing and painting.

36:17.575 --> 36:19.811
        Good morning.
[ Chittering ]

36:21.246 --> 36:24.082
Mr. Neilson, you sure
are the cleverest monkey...

36:24.149 --> 36:27.986
for painting all
these beautiful pictures.
Thank you very much.

36:28.053 --> 36:31.856
    And the dearest.
Ohh!

36:31.923 --> 36:33.858
What about me?

36:33.925 --> 36:35.927
That's enough.

36:38.096 --> 36:42.467
                [ Mumbles ]
Oh, hello, Alfonso.

36:42.534 --> 36:46.738
I love you too, Alfonso.
I'm so lucky to have
you guys.

36:46.805 --> 36:49.541
Got her, boss!
    Outta there!

36:51.543 --> 36:56.848
Ah, there she is.
Turning my property
into a pigsty.

36:56.915 --> 36:59.017
Ain't yours yet, boss.
[ Laughing ]

36:59.084 --> 37:03.655
No, but it soon will be
if you two idiots
do your stuff.

37:06.057 --> 37:09.761
Listen. She loves
those two stinking animals,
doesn't she?

37:09.828 --> 37:11.830
Right, right.
            [ Laughing ]

37:11.896 --> 37:15.200
Hello. I'm coming.
         <i>[ Tommy ]</i>
         <i>Come on, Pippi.</i>

37:15.266 --> 37:18.770
There's rocks ahead.
Don't worry.

37:21.272 --> 37:24.642
                     <i>Catch!</i>
Oh! Oh, my gosh!

37:24.709 --> 37:27.412
They don't make china
like they used to.

37:29.247 --> 37:31.282
Don't miss these!

37:34.319 --> 37:37.555
What a bozo!
I work my fingers
to the bone cooking for you,

37:37.622 --> 37:40.091
and you mess it all up!

37:41.593 --> 37:43.695
Here's yours.

37:43.762 --> 37:46.865
Oh, thank you.

37:46.931 --> 37:51.436
    Isn't it great to be alive?
What in the world did we do
before Pippi came?

37:51.503 --> 37:55.306
Practically nothing.
Fished, read comics,
played ball.

37:55.373 --> 37:58.209
But now every day
is fantastic.

38:01.813 --> 38:04.082
It's one of those
"perodactyl" things.

38:04.149 --> 38:07.952
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>That's Jake and</i>
<i>his new flying machine.</i>

38:08.019 --> 38:10.789
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Gee, I've never seen anything</i>
<i>like that before.</i>

38:10.855 --> 38:14.359
- He invented it himself.
- You mean he actually
  made that thing?

38:14.425 --> 38:16.795
He calls it his autogiro.

38:16.861 --> 38:21.900
He even promised me and Annika
he'd take us up sometime.
Except Dad says no way.

38:21.966 --> 38:23.935
He thinks
it's too dangerous.

38:26.437 --> 38:29.440
<i>[ Man Laughs ]</i>
<i>There it is, boss.</i>

38:29.507 --> 38:31.976
Look, I can fly.

38:32.043 --> 38:34.245
Pippi, don't!
You'll fall!
        You can't really fly!

38:34.312 --> 38:39.184
My papa always says that
if you believe in yourself,
you can do anything.

38:39.250 --> 38:42.620
- <i>[ Ringing Noise ]</i>
- Shoot. That's Mom.

38:42.687 --> 38:46.925
- <i>We gotta go now. We promised.</i>
- Bye!

38:46.991 --> 38:49.160
Bye.

38:49.227 --> 38:51.663
Leave it to us, boss.
Come on. Let's go.
            Okay.

38:51.729 --> 38:53.698
Pippi, there are two
official-looking guys...

38:53.765 --> 38:56.434
coming through the gate
with white jackets on.

38:56.501 --> 39:01.506
Fantastic.
I just love men in uniform.

39:01.573 --> 39:03.675
But policemen are the best.

39:05.643 --> 39:07.745
Ouch!
    Shh!

39:10.215 --> 39:12.784
        [ Knocking ]
Anyone home?

39:14.385 --> 39:18.823
County Animal Control.
Come to fix your livestock.

39:18.890 --> 39:20.925
[ Both Laughing ]

39:22.594 --> 39:24.562
[ Chittering ]

39:26.598 --> 39:28.399
Hey. What are you doing?
What are you doing?

39:30.235 --> 39:31.970
                Wow!
Oh!

39:33.972 --> 39:36.007
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Watch it!</i>

39:36.074 --> 39:41.713
That's pirates' gold.
And anyone who touches it
will turn to dust.

39:41.779 --> 39:45.717
Look, kid, we got an order
to take your animals
for their shots.

39:45.783 --> 39:47.952
Nobody shoots my animals.

39:48.019 --> 39:50.455
Whoa, whoa.
We're not gonna shoot 'em.

39:50.521 --> 39:52.957
We're just gonna
give 'em a few jabs.
                        Yeah.

39:54.759 --> 39:56.661
<i>Hey, that's my rope!</i>

39:58.196 --> 40:01.132
That's it, kid!
Aaaah!

40:01.199 --> 40:04.068
Okay, kid, if
that's the way you want it!

40:04.135 --> 40:06.371
<i>[ Crashing ]</i>

40:09.540 --> 40:12.143
- Whoa!
- Ohhhh!

40:12.210 --> 40:16.481
And that's the bully tree.
You should be ashamed,
picking on a poor little girl.

40:16.547 --> 40:19.717
Ohhh!

40:19.784 --> 40:23.855
No sense wasting
such a nice day.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.624
You little monster, you!

40:26.691 --> 40:30.028
- Let's play "find the hat."
- Come here, you!
  [ Yells ]

40:31.696 --> 40:32.730
Come and get it!

40:32.797 --> 40:35.300
Let's get the gold
and get out of here.

40:35.366 --> 40:38.803
What? With her yelling
her head off
in full view of everyone?

40:38.870 --> 40:41.072
Get that ladder!

40:41.139 --> 40:43.474
That's the idea.
The view's lovely up here.

40:43.541 --> 40:48.646
I'm gonna get that
strong-armed little freak
if it's the last thing I do.

40:48.713 --> 40:53.551
        Then what?
        They've seen our faces.
Here's what we'll do.

40:53.618 --> 40:58.756
We'll put her in the sack,
and when it gets dark,
we'll get rid of her.

41:02.193 --> 41:05.363
- Here. Don't want you
  to get sunstroke.
- [ Yells ]

41:05.430 --> 41:07.865
    Get up there!
    Go on!
[ Mumbling ]

41:09.567 --> 41:13.037
Bravo! Well done.
Isn't this fun?
I do it every day.

41:13.104 --> 41:18.042
You little brat!
I'm going to pull those
pigtails clear to China.

41:18.109 --> 41:20.578
- Come on, kid!
- <i>[ Pippi Laughing ]</i>

41:30.588 --> 41:32.991
[ Yelling ]

41:33.057 --> 41:36.194
Get off me! Get off me!
Let go!

41:36.260 --> 41:39.097
Let go!
You've had your fun.

41:39.163 --> 41:42.100
What's wrong?
I thought it was
just a game.

41:42.166 --> 41:44.669
<i>When we're finished,</i>
<i>we can have a feast</i>
<i>of Coke and cookies.</i>

41:44.736 --> 41:48.539
Put the ladder here, kid,
and we'll call it a day.

41:48.606 --> 41:52.343
<i>[ Men Shouting ]</i>

41:52.410 --> 41:55.246
Hurry!
Come on! Move it!
Get out of my way!

41:57.815 --> 42:00.918
[ Yelling ]

42:00.985 --> 42:03.287
        You idiot!
Why, you little--

42:03.354 --> 42:05.323
<i>You go for her.</i>
<i>Get her off that horse.</i>

42:05.390 --> 42:08.459
- I'll get you now!
- [ Whinnies ]

42:08.526 --> 42:11.462
- <i>[ Alfonso ]</i>
 <i>I'll get you.</i>
- [ Yelling ]

42:11.529 --> 42:15.400
<i>Let's get outta here.</i>
<i>This is more trouble</i>
<i>than a truckload of baboons!</i>

42:15.466 --> 42:17.535
Oh! Oh-oh!

42:17.602 --> 42:20.238
               [ Chittering ]
<i>[ Yelling Continues ]</i>

42:20.304 --> 42:22.240
They're never gonna
separate us.

42:22.306 --> 42:25.543
Uh-uh. Never,
never, never!

42:25.610 --> 42:28.413
All you had to do
was grab the horse
and the monkey!

42:28.479 --> 42:30.782
We would've been rid
of her forever!

42:30.848 --> 42:34.018
d all that money
just lying there!

42:34.085 --> 42:38.423
Be back in a couple hours.

42:38.489 --> 42:42.894
Get, get down!
Come on. Get out of there!

42:42.960 --> 42:47.098
It's not safe now.
Come on.
What are you doing up here?

42:47.165 --> 42:49.667
I just wanted to see
what it was like to fly.

42:49.734 --> 42:52.804
Careful, careful, careful.
It's dangerous.

42:52.870 --> 42:55.740
            They could take
            your head off.
Who cares?

42:55.807 --> 43:01.079
I once ran into
a headless pirate in Istanbul.
He never knew which way was up.

43:01.145 --> 43:05.983
Well, I'm afraid you're
gonna have to wait a few
years to fly an autogiro.

43:06.050 --> 43:09.687
Yeah, you know,
I risk my life
every time I go up.

43:12.457 --> 43:15.193
Vroom! Vroom! Vroom!

43:15.259 --> 43:18.429
That's it.
 That's the idea.

43:18.496 --> 43:20.765
Vroom! Vroom!

43:20.832 --> 43:24.202
Is that all
there is to it?
        No, no, of course not!

43:24.268 --> 43:27.705
Uh, see, you need these
to keep you up...

43:27.772 --> 43:30.842
and the prop
to take you forward.

43:30.908 --> 43:34.779
But it's really a lot more
complicated than that.

43:34.846 --> 43:38.249
Well, I bet
I could do it.

43:38.316 --> 43:41.285
Can I watch you
take off?
                Sure!

43:41.352 --> 43:44.489
And feel free
to come around any time.

43:44.555 --> 43:47.892
I always feel free.
Thanks. Bye.

43:50.828 --> 43:52.763
Bye!

43:59.537 --> 44:02.173
[ Laughing ]

44:12.316 --> 44:15.520
My pop and I have been
shipwrecked so many times...

44:15.586 --> 44:19.323
that there are only eight
or nine islands we haven't
been to in the whole world.

44:19.390 --> 44:21.325
Weren't you afraid?

44:21.392 --> 44:25.630
Well, there was this hurricane,
and the peas flew out
of the soup.

44:25.696 --> 44:29.767
And the ship's cat
flew past me stark naked,

44:29.834 --> 44:31.969
and his fur landed
on my fork.

44:39.143 --> 44:42.213
Excu-- What do you think
you're doing?

44:42.280 --> 44:45.983
The sugar feels sensational
between your toes.

44:46.050 --> 44:48.886
I'm sorry, but we just
don't behave that way
in this household.

44:48.953 --> 44:50.888
Sorry.

44:52.223 --> 44:54.325
[ Clears Throat ]
Now, tell me,

44:54.392 --> 44:56.861
what makes you think
that your father
is still alive?

44:56.928 --> 45:01.666
I know he is.
He'll be back soon.
You can rely on that.

45:01.732 --> 45:04.101
Ahhh.

45:15.446 --> 45:19.050
I can't see a thing!

45:19.116 --> 45:23.721
Pippi, come in the kitchen.
We'll wipe off your face.
It'll be all right.

45:23.788 --> 45:25.790
I think I went a little
too far.

45:25.856 --> 45:30.895
That wasn't funny, Pippi.
Your table manners
are atrocious.

45:30.962 --> 45:35.166
Listen, if I promise
to practice one hour each day,

45:35.233 --> 45:38.002
will you teach me all
that table manners and stuff?

45:38.069 --> 45:40.004
I'll try.

45:40.071 --> 45:42.907
Now I want the real truth.

45:42.974 --> 45:46.410
Your mother--
She is dead, isn't she?

45:46.477 --> 45:48.379
Oh, no!

45:54.118 --> 45:57.788
[ Gasps ]
You see that cloud?

45:57.855 --> 46:01.792
Well, there's
a little hole in it
right above my house.

46:01.859 --> 46:04.895
Whenever I'm in trouble
or I need advice,

46:04.962 --> 46:08.366
I see her face
right about there.

46:08.432 --> 46:11.569
She always helps me
one way or another.

46:16.007 --> 46:18.342
You okay, Pippi?
    You want to play upstairs?

46:18.409 --> 46:22.046
I can't.
Alfonso's dying
for a hay soufflé,

46:22.113 --> 46:24.682
and Mr. Neilson wants
a banana split.

46:24.749 --> 46:27.818
<i>Good night.</i>
<i>Don't let the bedbugs bite.</i>

46:31.155 --> 46:33.457
Oh, wait, oh.
Hold it, kids.
You hold on right there.

46:33.524 --> 46:35.593
I wanna talk to you.

46:35.660 --> 46:37.895
Just hang on there.
 Just hang on.

46:37.962 --> 46:41.499
Honey, I'm really worried
about Pippi.

46:41.565 --> 46:44.669
She's all alone
in that house. There's
no one to take care of her.

46:44.735 --> 46:49.507
Look, don't
get yourself all upset.
Pippi is not our responsibility.

46:49.573 --> 46:53.010
<i>This Miss Bannister,</i>
<i>she has a lot of support</i>
<i>in this town.</i>

46:53.077 --> 46:55.379
I can see why.

46:55.446 --> 47:01.218
The county created
the children's home for kids
who are lost or have no parents.

47:01.285 --> 47:02.953
And it--

47:03.020 --> 47:06.791
It just seems to me that Pippi
fits the bill perfectly.

47:06.857 --> 47:11.762
Poor Pippi.
No mother or father
to look after her.

47:11.829 --> 47:14.899
We've gotta do something.
Something drastic.

47:17.134 --> 47:19.870
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>The boxes are finished.</i>
<i>Where do we put them?</i>

47:19.937 --> 47:22.973
<i>[ Jake ] Be careful</i>
<i>how you mount them.</i>
<i>They gotta be fixed real firm.</i>

47:23.040 --> 47:25.843
<i>[ Sawing, Hammering Noise ]</i>
       What?

47:25.910 --> 47:27.745
Oh.

47:30.481 --> 47:34.185
Oh, this is too much.
This is just too much!

47:34.251 --> 47:38.422
What the heck
could she be doing
at 3:00 in the morning?

47:40.291 --> 47:42.360
Can we-- I say,

47:42.426 --> 47:47.598
can we possibly have
a little peace and quiet here?

47:47.665 --> 47:49.734
Go to bed!

47:49.800 --> 47:53.704
Don't fuss.
You're getting rid of her
tomorrow, aren't you?

47:53.771 --> 47:57.274
I wouldn't exactly say
that I'm getting rid of her.

47:57.341 --> 48:00.244
But, eh, eh--
What, you don't approve?

48:00.311 --> 48:04.582
You know I don't.
Not at all.

48:04.648 --> 48:06.684
<i>[ Hammering Continues ]</i>

48:06.751 --> 48:09.720
<i>[ Children ]</i>
<i>Twelve times sixteen...</i>

48:09.787 --> 48:13.257
<i>equals 192.</i>

48:13.324 --> 48:16.560
<i>[ Teacher ] Children, eyes</i>
<i>to the blackboard, please.</i>
   Tommy.

48:16.627 --> 48:20.564
Tommy?

48:20.631 --> 48:25.403
Twelve times twelve equals
one hundred and forty-four.
                    Annika?

48:25.469 --> 48:29.640
Pippi, how can I teach
arithmetic with you sitting
there? Please come inside.

48:29.707 --> 48:33.077
Well, I don't want
to upset you.
I'm just curious.

48:33.144 --> 48:35.913
<i>I've never been</i>
<i>to school before.</i>

48:35.980 --> 48:39.550
Except in Wagga Wagga.
That's in Australia.

48:39.617 --> 48:42.953
They chased wallabies
all day long.

48:43.020 --> 48:46.157
       And we had koala bears
       sitting in on--
<i>Enough, Pippi.</i>

48:46.223 --> 48:51.529
I'm afraid you can't stay there.
It's disrupting the class.
Children, back to your seats.

48:51.595 --> 48:55.366
I was just hoping
all that learning floating
around in there...

48:55.433 --> 48:59.170
might fly out here
and stick to me...
and Mr. Neilson.

48:59.236 --> 49:02.606
<i>He's very bad</i>
<i>with his numbers.</i>
                   Yeah.

49:02.673 --> 49:06.377
I'd like to help you,
but you make that impossible.

49:11.048 --> 49:15.686
Whenever you're ready, come
to school like everyone else,
and I'll teach you.

49:15.753 --> 49:19.390
But now we must press on.
                         <i>Bye.</i>

49:21.125 --> 49:23.327
Well, I guess we'll
just have to stay stupid.

49:23.394 --> 49:25.896
Oh, dear.

49:25.963 --> 49:30.301
Thank you. Will you wait here
for five minutes, please?

49:31.969 --> 49:36.207
[ Fire Truck Bells Clanging,
  Siren Wailing ]

49:40.010 --> 49:41.912
You have the order?
                Yes, yes, yes.

49:41.979 --> 49:44.448
Good. Then everything
is absolutely legal.

49:44.515 --> 49:48.652
Excuse me.
Is all this really necessary?
I mean, she's just a child.

49:48.719 --> 49:53.858
A child? I've seen
this child in action.
She's totally irresponsible.

49:53.924 --> 49:56.494
But a fire engine?
Now, why do we need that?

49:56.560 --> 50:02.333
Because the brat climbs up
on roofs and in trees.
And I've seen her up there.

50:02.399 --> 50:06.871
She is more slippery
than that filthy monkey
she lives with,

50:06.937 --> 50:10.774
    not to mention
    that stinking horse of hers.
Why the police?

50:10.841 --> 50:13.043
Oh, she's very strong.
You should see what
she did.

50:13.110 --> 50:16.480
She threw my men up in a tree.
Then she lifted me
like I was a baby.

50:16.547 --> 50:18.582
That's some baby,
I'll tell ya.

50:18.649 --> 50:22.219
I think you'll agree we have
to be prepared for anything
this girl may come up with.

50:22.286 --> 50:27.892
We are agreed.
Now, nobody wants to be
unfair or unkind to Pippi.

50:27.958 --> 50:30.361
But I think that once
she is safe in the van,

50:30.427 --> 50:34.431
then the whole town
can just breathe
a sigh of relief.

50:38.869 --> 50:42.506
[ Siren Wailing ]

50:50.648 --> 50:53.150
[ Siren Wailing ]
            [ Bell Clanging ]

50:53.217 --> 50:55.386
Tommy, Annika!

50:59.623 --> 51:01.425
<i>Pippi,</i>
<i>they're comin' for you!</i>

51:01.492 --> 51:06.730
The police, the fire engine,
Miss Bannister!
Just about everyone.

51:06.797 --> 51:10.334
<i>I bet my father's</i>
<i>with them too.</i>
<i>They can't take you, Pippi.</i>

51:10.401 --> 51:13.470
We're going to run away.
Please come with us.

51:13.537 --> 51:17.908
Yeah, come with us.
Mom and Dad are trying
 ruin everything for us.

51:17.975 --> 51:21.712
Well, I've never run away
from anything.

51:21.779 --> 51:24.548
But I can't let you guys
go off on your own.

51:24.615 --> 51:27.585
So I guess I'll have
to come with ya.
Let's go.

51:27.651 --> 51:29.720
Good luck!
 <i>Thanks, freckle-face.</i>

51:29.787 --> 51:32.556
[ Tommy ]
How we gonna run away?

51:32.623 --> 51:36.727
It just so happens I might have
exactly what we need.

51:36.794 --> 51:40.631
[ Siren Wailing ]
    [ Bell Clanging ]

51:57.715 --> 52:01.051
<i>[ Whirring,</i>
<i> Clattering Noise ]</i>

52:10.995 --> 52:12.696
Good God!
Look at that!

52:14.832 --> 52:20.104
- All right!
- Get-Get out! Get out!
- We'll go after her!

52:20.170 --> 52:22.406
<i>If I could fly,</i>
<i>I could catch them!</i>

52:36.220 --> 52:37.821
[ Siren Wailing ]

52:40.691 --> 52:41.859
Oh, my God!

52:43.494 --> 52:46.930
<i>Keep pedaling.</i>
<i>I'll bring it up.</i>

52:48.465 --> 52:54.004
- Up, up, up!
- Up! Up!

53:05.482 --> 53:07.418
Up! Up!

53:07.484 --> 53:10.587
[ Pippi And Kids ]
 Flying off
  to who knows where

53:10.654 --> 53:14.892
The very air
 we breathe is sweet

53:14.958 --> 53:22.466
Up above the treetops
 there is not a challenge
 we can't meet

53:22.533 --> 53:26.637
<i>If it takes all day</i>
<i> or maybe longer </i>

53:26.704 --> 53:29.206
<i>If it takes all night</i>

53:31.008 --> 53:34.545
<i>We will make our way</i>
<i> We're gettin' stronger</i>

53:34.611 --> 53:37.548
<i>Freedom is worth the fight</i>

53:37.614 --> 53:40.317
Running away

53:40.384 --> 53:42.486
                   Up!
Running away

53:42.553 --> 53:44.588
Up! Up!

53:44.655 --> 53:47.257
<i>Running away</i>

53:48.992 --> 53:51.328
We're running away

53:57.401 --> 53:59.103
[ Chittering ]

54:03.841 --> 54:05.509
<i>Uh-oh.</i>

54:07.911 --> 54:09.980
What the heck
is she doing now?

54:10.047 --> 54:13.117
    You want us to take her,
    boss?
Can we, boss? Please, boss?

54:13.183 --> 54:15.986
<i>Please?</i>

54:16.053 --> 54:18.055
[ Nickering ]

54:20.724 --> 54:24.128
[ Sighs ]
Oh, Pippi.

54:24.194 --> 54:27.297
How could you have done this
to us?

54:27.364 --> 54:31.068
I always thought the kids
would be perfectly safe
with you.

54:31.135 --> 54:34.138
That you'd look
after them... somehow.

54:38.675 --> 54:42.146
   Here, boy.
   Come on. Come on.
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

54:42.212 --> 54:46.617
[ Father ]
Stop this thing now.
Make it-- Come on.

54:46.683 --> 54:50.921
Will you please stop
this dang-dong bell? Stop it!

54:52.723 --> 54:55.025
            Did you find them?
Not a trace.

54:55.092 --> 54:56.894
Boy, that Pippi
has really done it this time.

54:56.960 --> 54:59.163
Are you sure they were flying?

54:59.229 --> 55:03.600
-Looked like a flying bed to me.
-A bicycle.
 She was definitely pedaling.

55:03.667 --> 55:07.271
No! When it passed
my place, it looked li
that autogiro thing Jake built.

55:07.337 --> 55:09.840
Then let's go see
that crazy flying goon!

55:09.907 --> 55:14.912
-Come on. Let's get outta here.
-Stick around. Don't leave
 in case they come back.

55:14.978 --> 55:18.215
<i>[ Fire Chief ]</i>
<i>Watch out!</i>
<i>Don't hit the horses!</i>

55:21.585 --> 55:23.954
[ Siren Wailing ]
    [ Horses Whinnying ]

55:33.063 --> 55:36.533
I'm starving!
What are you doing, Pippi?

55:36.600 --> 55:39.536
I learned this
from a native in Borneo.
Don't worry. It'll work.

55:42.706 --> 55:45.542
<i>It'll work fine.</i>

55:49.580 --> 55:51.014
See? It works!

55:51.081 --> 55:55.319
- Wow! It really did work.
- <i>[ Pippi ] No sweat.</i>

55:55.385 --> 55:58.689
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>What are we gonna eat, Pippi?</i>
<i>What have you got in there?</i>

55:58.755 --> 56:02.459
Catch.
I don't feel like
hunting tonight.

56:02.526 --> 56:04.628
What would you hunt here
anyway, Pippi?

56:04.695 --> 56:09.700
Oh, lions, tigers...
and cannibals.

56:11.401 --> 56:13.503
I'm very good
with cannibals.

56:13.570 --> 56:16.506
Cannibals? Here?

56:16.573 --> 56:19.409
Just in case.

56:21.211 --> 56:26.083
It's very quiet.
You don't think
it's too quiet, do you?

56:26.149 --> 56:30.721
I promise you,
with this old gun,
I'll be able to defend us.

56:30.787 --> 56:33.156
Even if we should
be attacked by a splunk!

56:35.626 --> 56:36.894
[ Laughing ]

56:36.960 --> 56:40.731
Oh, I'm gonna go
take a nap.

56:40.797 --> 56:42.666
Wake me if you need me.

56:45.135 --> 56:48.438
And keep your eyes peeled.

56:48.505 --> 56:49.907
[ Laughing ]

56:51.141 --> 56:53.710
<i>[ Screeching ]</i>

56:53.777 --> 56:56.480
<i>[ Bird Squawking ]</i>

56:56.546 --> 57:01.451
<i>[ Growling ]</i>

57:02.618 --> 57:04.987
[ Rustling ]
             <i>[ Annika ]</i>
             <i>Pippi!</i>

57:05.054 --> 57:09.992
Pippi!

57:10.059 --> 57:13.662
There.
What did I tell you? It
could be a cannibal snooping.

57:13.729 --> 57:16.866
<i>You can never</i>
<i>be too careful.</i>

57:16.932 --> 57:20.202
Wouldn't be much use
running away if we're just
to be served up for dinner...

57:20.269 --> 57:24.173
with carrots and parsley.

57:24.240 --> 57:27.076
I'll bet they're looking
through their cookbooks
right now,

57:27.143 --> 57:29.845
learning how to make us
in a special stew.

57:29.912 --> 57:34.383
<i>But I'll tell you this:</i>
<i>If they ever put me...</i>

57:34.450 --> 57:37.253
on the same plate
as spinach--

57:37.319 --> 57:39.488
Yech!

57:39.555 --> 57:43.893
I will never,
ever forgive them.

57:43.959 --> 57:47.897
Oh, Pippi,
don't talk like that.

57:47.963 --> 57:50.266
<i>[ Distant Roaring ]</i>

57:55.004 --> 57:58.107
        <i>[ Annika ] Jeepers!</i>
        <i>What was that?</i>
<i>[ Animal Exhaling Loudly ]</i>

57:58.174 --> 58:00.976
[ Simulating Gunfire ]

58:04.447 --> 58:08.784
- <i>[ Tommy ] She shot it!</i>
- Three of them
  just bit the dust.

58:12.421 --> 58:16.258
Pippi, when I grow up,
I'm gonna be a pirate,
just like you.

58:16.325 --> 58:19.295
Swell. And
we'll be the terrors
of the Caribbean.

58:19.361 --> 58:23.532
We'll plunder gold and jewels
and hide our treasures
in a cave...

58:23.599 --> 58:26.435
with three skeletons
guarding it!

58:26.502 --> 58:30.673
                And we'll sing--
[ Together ]
 Life is a breeze
  We live it for fun

58:30.739 --> 58:34.410
<i>No apologies to anyone</i>

58:34.477 --> 58:38.180
<i>We live on the seas</i>
<i>  We do as we please</i>

58:38.247 --> 58:44.019
You've got it!
And everyone would turn pale and
throw themselves into the sea...

58:44.086 --> 58:49.625
to escape our bloody,
bloody revenge!

58:49.692 --> 58:53.395
What about me?
I don't dare
become a pirate.

58:53.462 --> 58:56.632
Well, you can come along
for the ride and dust the piano.

58:56.699 --> 59:02.104
- Dust the piano?
- Look what I found.

59:02.171 --> 59:04.640
From a shipwrecked sailor's
secret stash.
 <i>[ Annika ] Thanks.</i>

59:06.242 --> 59:09.245
Sleep tight.
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

59:13.115 --> 59:16.552
<i>[ Pippi Sighing ]</i>

59:16.619 --> 59:20.156
Darn it! We forgot
to brush our teeth.

59:20.222 --> 59:23.459
<i>[ Annika ]</i>
<i>Go to sleep.</i>

59:23.526 --> 59:28.130
Without your help, darn it,
Pippi never would've been able
to build that contraption.

59:28.197 --> 59:32.935
I know. And I'm willing
to help, but it's night.
        We'll use searchlights.

59:33.002 --> 59:37.239
Even if I could
get the autogiro up in the dark,
I could never land it.

59:37.306 --> 59:40.809
       [ Man ] We gotta
       find those kids somehow.
<i>[ Man #2 ] It's all your fault.</i>

59:40.876 --> 59:45.981
    Listen, guys--
[ Man ] You gotta help, Jake,
or we'll run you out of town.

59:46.048 --> 59:50.753
If you're not too scared to fly,
I'll take you up at first light,

59:50.819 --> 59:54.456
and we'll look in places
these guys could never go,
okay?
                    Okay.

01:00:10.005 --> 01:00:14.777
What's for breakfast?
     <i>[ Pippi ] Dinosaur eggs,</i>
     <i>sunny-side up.</i>

01:00:14.843 --> 01:00:18.614
Pippi! The plane!
It's sinking!

01:00:18.681 --> 01:00:22.518
How will we ever get back?
    We're supposed to be
    running away, aren't we?

01:00:22.585 --> 01:00:25.955
We're lost.
I want my mom.

01:00:26.021 --> 01:00:31.527
- We can't stay gone forever.
- Robinson Crusoe did.
  He stayed for seven years.

01:00:31.594 --> 01:00:36.365
- Seven years?
- I don't wanna stay that long.

01:00:36.432 --> 01:00:39.468
Three years, okay?
Whew.

01:00:39.535 --> 01:00:45.207
It's getting hot.
Wanna go for a swim
before breakfast?

01:00:45.274 --> 01:00:48.177
<i>Come on!</i>

01:00:56.352 --> 01:01:00.889
<i>Pippi, you still</i>
<i>got all your clothes on!</i>

01:01:02.224 --> 01:01:05.761
I know.
It's more fun this way.

01:01:08.530 --> 01:01:11.133
They can't
have gone this far!

01:01:11.200 --> 01:01:14.336
Hey! Don't forget!
They have one
of my flying machines!

01:01:19.608 --> 01:01:22.411
[ All Screeching ]

01:01:30.886 --> 01:01:33.856
[ Screeching Continues ]

01:01:36.659 --> 01:01:41.463
Hey, listen.
I'm the killer whale, and
you're the shipwrecked kids!

01:01:43.799 --> 01:01:47.069
[ Pippi ]
Race you to shore.

01:01:47.136 --> 01:01:50.272
<i>[ All Giggling ]</i>

01:01:53.642 --> 01:01:58.013
- [ Annika ]
  These stones hurt my feet.
- [ Tommy ] Always complaining.

01:01:58.080 --> 01:02:01.183
[ Tommy ]
Come on.

01:02:01.250 --> 01:02:04.219
Oh, no! Our clothes!
They're gone!

01:02:04.286 --> 01:02:08.390
        Somebody's taken them.
They have
to be here somewhere.

01:02:08.457 --> 01:02:12.795
The dinosaur, I guess.
A fair exchange
for the eggs.

01:02:12.861 --> 01:02:18.067
Now you know why I swim
with my clothes on.
    What are we gonna do?

01:02:26.241 --> 01:02:28.210
Nah.

01:02:28.277 --> 01:02:31.146
[ Whistles ]
Sit down!

01:02:31.213 --> 01:02:34.316
You'll either
lose your head
or make us crash.

01:02:34.383 --> 01:02:38.921
There's no sign of them!
Go back to the lake!

01:02:38.987 --> 01:02:43.025
If I know Pippi,
she'll be finding some way
back home!

01:02:43.092 --> 01:02:46.528
[ All ]
 If it takes all day
  or maybe longer

01:02:46.595 --> 01:02:49.965
If it takes all night

01:02:50.032 --> 01:02:54.303
We will make our way
 We're gettin' stronger

01:02:54.370 --> 01:02:57.272
Freedom is worth the fight

01:02:57.339 --> 01:02:59.441
Runnin' away

01:03:01.176 --> 01:03:04.346
Runnin' away

01:03:04.413 --> 01:03:07.216
We're saved!

01:03:07.282 --> 01:03:10.953
[ Tommy ] What do you mean,
we're saved, Pippi?
    [ Pippi ] You'll see.

01:03:16.558 --> 01:03:18.894
Never gonna find 'em.

01:03:20.763 --> 01:03:24.066
[ Whistles ]
I'm gonna follow that river!

01:03:28.303 --> 01:03:31.874
[ Pippi ]
This is as safe
as taking a Sunday stroll.

01:03:31.940 --> 01:03:36.178
I once knew a guy who
went down the Niagara Falls
in a barrel.

01:03:36.245 --> 01:03:39.148
He said it was fantastic.

01:03:39.214 --> 01:03:42.351
[ All ]
 Tiny people on the ground

01:03:42.418 --> 01:03:46.355
We're too high up
 to hear them scream

01:03:46.422 --> 01:03:50.159
Tryin' hard
 to pull us down

01:03:50.225 --> 01:03:54.396
They have forgotten
 how to dream

01:03:54.463 --> 01:03:58.634
Runnin' until we drop
 or maybe longer

01:03:58.700 --> 01:04:02.104
Runnin' until we win

01:04:02.171 --> 01:04:06.241
We'll end up on top
 There's no one stronger

01:04:06.308 --> 01:04:09.144
That's the mood we're in

01:04:09.211 --> 01:04:11.647
Runnin' away

01:04:13.382 --> 01:04:14.750
Runnin' away

01:04:17.820 --> 01:04:21.623
Hey, there!
Turn around!
Turn around!

01:04:21.690 --> 01:04:24.593
        [ Tommy ]
        You okay, Pippi?
[ Pippi ] I'm fantastic.

01:04:24.660 --> 01:04:27.463
[ Tommy ]
Is this safe?
    Pippi, I'm scared.

01:04:27.529 --> 01:04:30.833
        Hold on. Don't worry.
What's that big noise
up there?

01:04:33.101 --> 01:04:36.738
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>It must be a waterfall, but</i>
<i>it can't be as big as Niagara.</i>

01:04:36.805 --> 01:04:40.876
   Grab hold of the paddle!
   Hurry!
<i>[ Annika Screams ]</i>

01:04:40.943 --> 01:04:43.779
I'm trying!
Help, Pippi!

01:04:43.846 --> 01:04:48.517
Get it! Hurry!
We'll come out on top
like we always do!

01:04:51.920 --> 01:04:55.958
[ Tommy ]
We're gonna go over the falls!
My barrel's leaking.

01:04:56.024 --> 01:05:00.696
<i>There they are-- down there!</i>
<i>I'll drop the ladder!</i>

01:05:00.762 --> 01:05:03.031
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>Help!</i>
<i>[ Annika Screaming ]</i>

01:05:04.833 --> 01:05:08.570
        I think we'll make it!
        Help!
[ Screaming ] Help!

01:05:08.637 --> 01:05:13.308
- [ Tommy ] Look!
  It's Jake! Help! Help!
- Go lower!

01:05:13.375 --> 01:05:16.378
<i>[ Kids ] Help! Help!</i>
<i>[ Jake ]</i>
<i>I'll go as low as I can.</i>

01:05:16.445 --> 01:05:19.081
[ All Shouting ]

01:05:19.147 --> 01:05:22.150
- <i>[ Tommy ]</i>
 <i>We're down here!</i>
- Hold it steady!

01:05:22.217 --> 01:05:25.787
- Yeah. Okay. I will.
- <i>[ Tommy ]</i>
 <i>Help! Help!</i>

01:05:25.854 --> 01:05:29.925
<i>Kids, kids, grab hold of it!</i>
<i>Grab hold of the ladder!</i>

01:05:29.992 --> 01:05:32.427
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>Help!</i>

01:05:32.494 --> 01:05:35.998
- [ Pippi ] Grab hold of it!
- [ Tommy ] I've got it!
- That's good! Stay there!

01:05:36.064 --> 01:05:40.602
[ Pippi ]
Come on! Get it, Tommy!

01:05:40.669 --> 01:05:43.305
Hold it steady!
    Don't move around so much!

01:05:43.372 --> 01:05:45.340
[ Pippi ]
Get ahold of it! Hang on!

01:05:53.382 --> 01:05:56.885
- <i>[ Tommy ]</i>
 <i>  Then Dad dropped the rope!</i>
- And Pippi grabbed ahold of it.

01:05:56.952 --> 01:06:02.124
    Then we got ahold of Pippi.
We all went swinging over
the treetops and fire engines.

01:06:02.190 --> 01:06:04.927
   And now you're
   making it up just like--
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

01:06:04.993 --> 01:06:08.230
And everybody
lived happily ever after.

01:06:08.297 --> 01:06:11.633
You know, when I grow up,
maybe I'm not gonna
be a pirate.

01:06:11.700 --> 01:06:15.337
I'm seriously thinking
of changing it to a pilot.

01:06:15.404 --> 01:06:18.373
Pippi, I don't think
you understand.

01:06:18.440 --> 01:06:21.510
You really
went too far this time.

01:06:21.577 --> 01:06:24.980
But there's
good old Villa Villekulla
still there.

01:06:25.047 --> 01:06:30.252
Nobody's been hurt, and we all
did things we've never done
before, and we had a ball.

01:06:30.319 --> 01:06:32.588
[ Siren
  Continues Wailing ]

01:06:37.092 --> 01:06:39.728
[ Kids ] Bye, Pippi!
Sleep tight! See you!

01:06:39.795 --> 01:06:42.731
Bye!
See you tomorrow!

01:06:42.798 --> 01:06:45.400
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>You got a neat fire engine.</i>

01:06:45.467 --> 01:06:50.305
Well, I hope
you're satisfied,
young lady.

01:06:50.372 --> 01:06:55.277
All those poor people
out of their beds and
out of their minds...

01:06:55.344 --> 01:06:58.680
because of your stupidity--
psst, psst, psst--

01:06:58.747 --> 01:07:02.084
and your irresponsibili--
bility.

01:07:02.150 --> 01:07:04.186
[ Mumbles ]

01:07:05.754 --> 01:07:08.790
Hi, Alfonso.
You okay?
        [ Whinnying ]

01:07:10.759 --> 01:07:14.463
You know, quite often,
people go to bed
too early anyway...

01:07:14.529 --> 01:07:17.165
just because they haven't
had anything exciting
to do.

01:07:17.232 --> 01:07:19.067
[ Groans ]

01:07:21.269 --> 01:07:25.173
I do wish
I'd asked that nice man for
a ride on his fire engine.

01:07:25.240 --> 01:07:27.943
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>
<i>Do you realize</i>
<i>all those people...</i>

01:07:28.010 --> 01:07:31.713
<i>have lost time and money</i>
<i>searching for you?</i>

01:07:31.780 --> 01:07:35.651
Well,
if that's the only problem,
I've got tons of gold inside.

01:07:35.717 --> 01:07:37.953
<i>Come on in.</i>

01:07:38.020 --> 01:07:41.390
<i>I don't want anybody</i>
<i>to be unhappy,</i>

01:07:41.456 --> 01:07:45.260
<i>so they can each</i>
<i>have two gold coins</i>
<i>from the Spanish Main...</i>

01:07:45.327 --> 01:07:47.496
to remind them
of this fantastic day.

01:07:49.264 --> 01:07:54.136
[ Groans ]
This place.
It's still a pigsty.

01:07:54.202 --> 01:07:58.440
- <i>It's worse than ever.</i>
- <i>[ Pippi ] When you've been</i>
  on an expedition like we were,

01:07:58.507 --> 01:08:01.376
you expect things
to get a little dusty.

01:08:03.645 --> 01:08:06.782
               You see?
<i>[ Coins Clatter</i>
<i> To Ground ]</i>

01:08:06.848 --> 01:08:09.685
                What day is it?
It's Friday.

01:08:09.751 --> 01:08:11.953
Great.

01:08:12.020 --> 01:08:15.190
    I can start spring cleaning.
    You can help too.
Hmm?

01:08:15.257 --> 01:08:18.926
Don't you realize
that it's 2:00 in the morning?

01:08:18.993 --> 01:08:21.763
All normal children
are in bed.

01:08:23.198 --> 01:08:26.234
Pippi, dear,
you can't go on like this.

01:08:26.301 --> 01:08:30.439
                You're worn out.
                 You're dirty.
[ Yawning ]

01:08:30.505 --> 01:08:33.875
And you have no sense
of values.

01:08:37.446 --> 01:08:41.316
Now, I want you
to listen just once--
just once.

01:08:43.618 --> 01:08:46.354
We have this home...

01:08:46.421 --> 01:08:52.160
where children like you
are looked after when they
have no mothers or fathers.

01:08:52.227 --> 01:08:56.430
Now, I have the power
to force you--

01:08:58.734 --> 01:09:03.738
I urge you
to come along peacefully.

01:09:03.805 --> 01:09:07.509
<i>This is for your own good.</i>
<i>Now, please.</i>

01:09:07.576 --> 01:09:11.145
Just try.
 Just, say, till Christmas?

01:09:11.212 --> 01:09:14.282
Can I ride the fire engine?

01:09:16.551 --> 01:09:19.554
If that's what it takes.

01:09:19.621 --> 01:09:22.457
Just till Christmas.

01:09:27.429 --> 01:09:29.397
[ Sighs ]

01:09:29.464 --> 01:09:34.102
Don't worry, Counselor.
I'll keep my eye on her.

01:09:34.169 --> 01:09:37.939
Boy, I hope we've done
the right thing. My children
are just gonna hate me.

01:09:38.006 --> 01:09:42.978
They'll adjust, like
well must eventually.
[ Chuckles ]

01:09:43.044 --> 01:09:46.247
        Thank you for your help.
         Thank you.
Yeah, and thank you.

01:09:46.314 --> 01:09:50.652
Mr. Settigren, excuse me.
Any luck with the search?

01:09:50.719 --> 01:09:54.389
[ Sighs ] No. No.
I can't seem to find any record
of a sea captain...

01:09:54.456 --> 01:09:57.292
with the name of "Efraim"
or "Longstocking."

01:09:57.359 --> 01:10:01.797
And the Coast Guard registry
doesn't have any ship listed
under the name of <i>Hoptoad.</i>

01:10:01.863 --> 01:10:03.865
[ Wheezing Laugh ]

01:10:05.767 --> 01:10:10.539
However, I am going
to have a guard posted
at the Villa Villekulla...

01:10:10.605 --> 01:10:15.377
just in case anybody
gets any ideas
about any empty property,

01:10:15.443 --> 01:10:18.246
just until we get
to the bottom of this.

01:10:19.614 --> 01:10:22.450
- [ Engine Starts ]
- [ Both Laughing ]

01:10:25.120 --> 01:10:27.389
    Get off my car!
[ Grunts ]

01:10:32.227 --> 01:10:35.864
<i>[ Woman ] Class, I want you</i>
<i>to go to work on the 12</i>
<i>problems I've given you...</i>

01:10:35.931 --> 01:10:38.567
<i>while I go to work</i>
<i>on another little problem.</i>

01:10:38.633 --> 01:10:42.103
[ All ]
Yes, Miss Messerschmidt.

01:10:42.170 --> 01:10:46.474
<i>Pippilotta--</i>
<i>If that really is</i>
<i>your ridiculous name--</i>

01:10:46.541 --> 01:10:50.278
I want to know:
How much is 12 and 15?

01:10:50.345 --> 01:10:53.615
If you don't know something
as simple as that,
you shouldn't be teaching.

01:10:53.682 --> 01:10:57.686
- I won't stand
  for rudeness in this class.
- Then please sit down.

01:10:57.752 --> 01:11:03.558
I'm warning you, young lady.
We have ways of dealing
with rude, unruly children.

01:11:03.625 --> 01:11:07.796
- Haven't we, class?
- [ All ]
  Yes, Miss Messerschmidt.

01:11:07.863 --> 01:11:11.633
For your information,
12 and 15 are 27.

01:11:11.700 --> 01:11:14.836
But if you knew,
why did you ask me?

01:11:20.809 --> 01:11:23.311
Thirteen plus fourteen?

01:11:23.378 --> 01:11:26.548
Oh, about 67.

01:11:26.615 --> 01:11:28.817
No. It's 27.

01:11:28.884 --> 01:11:33.121
But you just said
12 and 15 was 27. I do wish
you'd make up your mind.

01:11:34.322 --> 01:11:36.424
Ouch! That hurt!

01:11:36.491 --> 01:11:39.694
That was my intention.
You've asked for it.

01:11:39.761 --> 01:11:44.165
Now, go over there,
and don't speak another word
till I give you permission.

01:11:52.841 --> 01:11:56.811
It's no good.
They won't even let her
come to the window.

01:11:56.878 --> 01:12:00.382
She's being disciplined.
        [ Tommy ]
        Poor Pippi.

01:12:00.448 --> 01:12:05.887
    Do you think
    we'll ever see her again?
Oh, I'm sure we will.

01:12:05.954 --> 01:12:08.723
<i>[ Children Laughing,</i>
<i>  Chattering ]</i>

01:12:08.790 --> 01:12:11.826
<i>[ Girl ]</i>
<i>Jennifer! Away!</i>

01:12:11.893 --> 01:12:15.363
<i>[ Girls Giggling ]</i>
<i>[ Girl ]</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>

01:12:18.934 --> 01:12:21.336
[ Girls Laughing ]

01:12:21.403 --> 01:12:24.839
        What'd you do that for?
You know very well.

01:12:26.374 --> 01:12:29.611
Hey, Pippi, you'll make
the pillow all dirty.

01:12:31.379 --> 01:12:35.183
In Australia,
everybody sleeps upside down.

01:12:35.250 --> 01:12:39.788
        [ All Laughing ]
I think it's time someone
told you that in Australia...

01:12:39.854 --> 01:12:42.290
<i>it's strictly against the law</i>
<i>to have lessons.</i>

01:12:42.357 --> 01:12:47.262
It may happen that one
Aussie kid might sneak into
his closet to study a lesson,

01:12:47.329 --> 01:12:50.665
but it's too bad
if his mother finds him.

01:12:50.732 --> 01:12:53.335
[ Scattered Giggling ]

01:12:53.401 --> 01:12:56.037
[ All ]
Whoa! How did you do that?

01:12:56.104 --> 01:12:59.708
Arithmetic--
They don't have
at all in China.

01:12:59.774 --> 01:13:02.410
If any kid knows
what 12 and 15 is,

01:13:02.477 --> 01:13:05.680
he'll have to stand
in the corner all day.

01:13:05.747 --> 01:13:09.284
If that's true,
what do they do all day
in school?

01:13:09.351 --> 01:13:12.287
Eat caramels.
There's a long pipe...

01:13:12.354 --> 01:13:15.290
that goes
from the caramel factory
right into the classroom.

01:13:15.357 --> 01:13:17.292
And it shoots candies
out of it all day long.

01:13:17.359 --> 01:13:22.364
- What does the teacher do?
- Takes the paper
  off the caramels for the kids.

01:13:22.430 --> 01:13:26.501
You don't think
they do it themselves!

01:13:26.568 --> 01:13:30.739
You're nothing
but a great, big liar, like
Miss Messerschmidt says.

01:13:30.805 --> 01:13:34.009
And who said you could
braid your hair again?

01:13:34.075 --> 01:13:39.614
Why are you so bossy
all the time? Don't you ever
do anything you wanna do?

01:13:39.681 --> 01:13:42.017
We were okay
until you came.

01:13:42.083 --> 01:13:44.185
But why would you want
to stay here?

01:13:44.252 --> 01:13:48.256
<i>They give us food and shelter,</i>
<i>and they take care of us.</i>

01:13:48.323 --> 01:13:52.394
Sometimes they're nice to us,
if we're good and do
as we're told.

01:13:52.460 --> 01:13:56.364
[ Screeches ] What are you
doing in here? Get out of
my dormitory, you naughty boys.

01:13:56.431 --> 01:13:58.867
<i>[ All Laughing ]</i>

01:13:58.933 --> 01:14:02.604
I don't understand.
            Well done, Pippi.

01:14:02.670 --> 01:14:05.106
I really don't understand.

01:14:12.080 --> 01:14:15.784
Pippi! How can you
make all this mess?

01:14:15.850 --> 01:14:19.187
<i>Wait till Miss Messerschmidt</i>
<i>sees what you've done.</i>

01:14:21.256 --> 01:14:26.428
Just think. How am I
supposed to draw a real horse
on a tiny piece of paper?

01:14:26.494 --> 01:14:31.399
- Miss Messerschmidt!
  Miss Messerschmidt!
- [ Mouthing Words ]

01:14:31.466 --> 01:14:35.737
- <i>Come quick! Come and see</i>
 <i>  what Pippi has done.</i>
- [ Boy ] Whoa!

01:14:35.804 --> 01:14:39.407
You. What do you think
you're doing?

01:14:39.474 --> 01:14:42.377
<i>I can't leave you alone</i>
<i>for five minutes without</i>
<i>your disrupting the class...</i>

01:14:42.444 --> 01:14:44.979
and defacing
the school premises.

01:14:45.046 --> 01:14:48.950
Back to your desks, class,
and carry on with your work.

01:14:53.221 --> 01:14:56.758
You see that little hut?
That's called the sweat box,

01:14:56.825 --> 01:14:59.828
<i>where really bad children</i>
<i>are put.</i>

01:15:09.104 --> 01:15:12.807
<i>Mom, I hope</i>
<i>you're not too busy up there,</i>

01:15:12.874 --> 01:15:15.443
you know,
playing the harp and all.

01:15:15.510 --> 01:15:17.712
But you know
what your Pippilotta's
been going through.

01:15:20.815 --> 01:15:25.887
Why do they
ask so many questions when
they already know the answers?

01:15:25.954 --> 01:15:28.723
I mean,
a horse is a horse.

01:15:30.091 --> 01:15:32.393
I'm so confused.

01:15:32.460 --> 01:15:35.864
If only Papa were here.
Then we'd know
the right thing to do.

01:15:37.699 --> 01:15:40.001
I wish he was.

01:15:41.436 --> 01:15:44.272
What? I didn't
quite hear you.

01:15:44.339 --> 01:15:49.310
Get a message to him?
But how?

01:15:51.045 --> 01:15:55.717
In a bottle?
Oh, thanks, Mom.
My problem's solved.

01:15:57.452 --> 01:16:02.023
Oh. You can go back
to playing your harp now.

01:16:08.363 --> 01:16:10.165
Shh.

01:16:13.868 --> 01:16:17.772
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Once, I had four jacks</i>
<i>and lost to four queens.</i>

01:16:17.839 --> 01:16:19.941
<i>It'll never happen again,</i>
<i>though.</i>

01:16:20.008 --> 01:16:23.878
<i>This little hand right here</i>
<i>should be enough to win.</i>

01:16:23.945 --> 01:16:26.848
            Yeah. Two bucks
            says you ain't got--
Flush.

01:16:26.915 --> 01:16:30.685
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Where'd you get that, huh?</i>
<i>Where'd you get them cards?</i>

01:16:30.752 --> 01:16:33.688
<i>[ Object Clanking ]</i>

01:16:49.204 --> 01:16:52.073
[ Cries Out, Muffled ]
                    Shh.

01:16:52.140 --> 01:16:55.176
What are
you doing here?

01:16:55.243 --> 01:16:59.681
What are you doing here?
You're not a ghost.

01:16:59.747 --> 01:17:04.552
I'm Greg,
of Gregory's Gripping Glue.
And I'm very sleepy.

01:17:04.619 --> 01:17:07.589
Well, there'plenty
of beds downstairs.

01:17:07.655 --> 01:17:10.592
[ Cans Rattling ]

01:17:10.658 --> 01:17:15.997
<i>How did you get up here?</i>
<i>You certainly didn't come</i>
<i>through the front door.</i>

01:17:18.566 --> 01:17:20.635
- I climbed up.
- On a ladder?

01:17:20.702 --> 01:17:23.338
No. Up the wall.

01:17:28.876 --> 01:17:32.547
            Up a drainpipe,
            I guess.
I walked up.

01:17:32.614 --> 01:17:37.885
Now you're telling whoppers
worse than me. Only flies
can walk up walls.

01:17:37.952 --> 01:17:40.488
And spiders and lizards
 and me!

01:17:40.555 --> 01:17:43.992
        How did you do it?
I'll show you.

01:17:44.058 --> 01:17:46.894
Give me your shoe.

01:17:50.365 --> 01:17:53.868
            What is that stuff?
This is a very special glue.

01:17:53.935 --> 01:17:56.237
Now the other one.

01:17:56.304 --> 01:18:00.575
It sticks when you want it to,
and it leaves go
when you're through.

01:18:00.642 --> 01:18:05.847
I invented it, and someday
I'm going to be very rich.

01:18:05.913 --> 01:18:09.751
            What do we do now?
Now you're going
to climb up the wall.

01:18:13.821 --> 01:18:17.425
<i>There. Go on.</i>
<i>You can do it.</i>

01:18:17.492 --> 01:18:21.129
[ Grunting ]
 <i>Well, go on.</i>

01:18:21.195 --> 01:18:23.865
I can't do it.

01:18:23.931 --> 01:18:27.802
Of course you can.
You can do almost anything
you want to...

01:18:27.869 --> 01:18:30.672
if you believe you can!

01:18:30.738 --> 01:18:33.608
That's what
I always used to say.

01:18:33.675 --> 01:18:35.977
Okay. Why not?

01:18:36.044 --> 01:18:39.013
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i> Sticky situation</i>

01:18:39.080 --> 01:18:43.017
 <i> My departure</i>
 <i>  has to be a fast one</i>
You're doing it!

01:18:43.084 --> 01:18:47.021
 <i> Sticky situation </i>
You're walking up the wall.

01:18:47.088 --> 01:18:50.191
<i>Every step is harder</i>
<i> than the last one </i>

01:18:53.027 --> 01:18:55.430
<i>Been in a lot of spots</i>

01:18:55.496 --> 01:19:00.134
<i>And had to use my ingenuity </i>
  Terrific!
   I'm walking on the ceiling!

01:19:00.201 --> 01:19:03.404
<i>The going gets too hot</i>

01:19:03.471 --> 01:19:08.176
<i>And soon the going</i>
<i> sees the last of me</i>

01:19:12.413 --> 01:19:14.749
You see?
No sweat!

01:19:14.816 --> 01:19:17.251
And it was fun!

01:19:17.318 --> 01:19:18.720
[ Wheezing Cough ]

01:19:21.756 --> 01:19:27.028
<i>Anyone up there? I don't know.</i>
<i>Those rats get bigger</i>
<i>every week.</i>

01:19:27.095 --> 01:19:29.597
<i>[ Metal Clanking ]</i>

01:19:32.767 --> 01:19:35.002
[ Whispers ]
Whoa.

01:19:36.471 --> 01:19:39.407
            Can you write?
Of course I can.

01:19:39.474 --> 01:19:42.577
But right now, I'm going
to take my little snooze.

01:19:42.643 --> 01:19:48.049
Listen, Mr. Gregory.
They don't know
I have this.

01:19:48.116 --> 01:19:51.686
But you can buy
just about anything
with it.

01:19:51.753 --> 01:19:55.656
If you'll stay awake long enough
to write me an S.O.S.,
it's yours.

01:19:55.723 --> 01:19:58.726
It's gold!
I don't want your money.

01:20:00.261 --> 01:20:02.797
What kind of an S.O.S.?
                    To my papa.

01:20:07.101 --> 01:20:09.303
Please write:

01:20:09.370 --> 01:20:13.307
"Pippilotta in the jam pot.
 Come quick. Villa Villekulla."

01:20:22.450 --> 01:20:25.686
It's a little bit
more difficult going down.

01:20:25.753 --> 01:20:28.456
Well, I can try.

01:20:28.523 --> 01:20:32.894
All right.
I'll put the note
in the bottle.

01:20:32.960 --> 01:20:35.830
Throw it down to me
when I get down
to the ground.

01:20:35.897 --> 01:20:38.966
All right.
        All right.
        Give me your hands.

01:20:39.033 --> 01:20:42.770
Just for the start.
Turn me around.

01:20:42.837 --> 01:20:47.041
Now, Gregory's Glue
won't let you down.

01:20:47.108 --> 01:20:51.946
<i>Now, just trust it.</i>
<i>Remember:</i>
<i>You must believe.</i>

01:20:52.013 --> 01:20:54.949
I'll try. Have a nice nap.
And thanks.

01:21:00.721 --> 01:21:02.757
[ Grunting ]

01:21:02.824 --> 01:21:05.026
You're doing it, Pippi.

01:21:06.761 --> 01:21:09.297
This is great.

01:21:09.363 --> 01:21:12.433
[ Grunting ]
     <i>Pippi, you're doing it!</i>

01:21:12.500 --> 01:21:17.572
- I told you--
  if you would just believe.
- [ Gasps ]

01:21:20.808 --> 01:21:22.443
Ohh.

01:21:25.146 --> 01:21:28.115
[ Whimpering ]

01:21:28.182 --> 01:21:30.184
- [ Grunts ]
- Oh.

01:21:38.426 --> 01:21:40.828
I can't move.
I'm stuck.

01:21:40.895 --> 01:21:44.198
Oh. Well, just jump.

01:21:44.265 --> 01:21:47.502
Papa always says
to leave room for your toes
to wiggle.

01:21:48.703 --> 01:21:51.639
Here we go!

01:21:52.907 --> 01:21:55.343
Thanks, Gregory.

01:22:04.452 --> 01:22:09.190
Now, I want you
to swim straight to my papa,
and no stops on the way.

01:22:12.293 --> 01:22:15.329
[ Whistling Through Air ]
         <i>Well, that's that.</i>

01:22:21.469 --> 01:22:25.239
- <i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>
- Oh, my gosh!

01:22:25.306 --> 01:22:27.608
<i>[ Siren Winds Down ]</i>

01:22:27.675 --> 01:22:30.278
Oh, my God! Fire!

01:22:30.344 --> 01:22:32.680
    [ All Shouting ]
[ Children ] Help! Fire!

01:22:32.747 --> 01:22:35.049
[ Gasps ]
Oh.

01:22:35.116 --> 01:22:40.354
[ Firefighter ]
All right! Get the hose off
and get that ladder over there!

01:22:40.421 --> 01:22:42.757
<i>Get the children out of there!</i>
<i>Hurry up!</i>

01:22:42.823 --> 01:22:46.294
- Please let me through!
  Let me through! Gregory!
- Help! I'm trapped!

01:22:46.360 --> 01:22:49.931
Don't worry, Gregory!
Pippi's back!

01:22:49.997 --> 01:22:53.768
<i>[ Gregory ]</i>
<i>The whole place is on fire!</i>
<i>Please help!</i>

01:22:53.834 --> 01:22:58.439
Hey, shoes, where are you?
I can't climb
without my shoes.

01:22:58.506 --> 01:23:02.076
[ Children Chattering,
  Crying ]

01:23:02.143 --> 01:23:05.046
        [ Officer ]
        How many more inside?
Oh, there are ten.

01:23:05.112 --> 01:23:10.551
<i>Oh, that Longstocking child!</i>
<i>Pippi, how did you get</i>
<i>down there?</i>

01:23:10.618 --> 01:23:13.521
My mom lent me her wings,
and I flew.
                     <i>Oh!</i>

01:23:13.588 --> 01:23:18.359
Can't you ever stop
telling those stories,
even at a time like this?

01:23:18.426 --> 01:23:23.030
There's a man up there, and
he surely doesn't have wings.

01:23:23.097 --> 01:23:26.434
 <i>[ People Screaming ]</i>
Come on, kids! Hurry, hurry!
Don't be frightened.

01:23:26.500 --> 01:23:29.103
Help!

01:23:29.170 --> 01:23:31.906
       [ Confused Chattering,
         Screaming ]
<i>[ Man ] Move those hoses!</i>

01:23:31.973 --> 01:23:35.776
<i>Volunteers to hold the net.</i>
<i>Come on! Come on! Come on!</i>

01:23:35.843 --> 01:23:40.381
<i>The ladder won't reach.</i>
<i>Don't worry, Gregory.</i>
<i>I'll save you.</i>

01:23:40.448 --> 01:23:44.919
- We're trapped!
- [ Firefighter ] You can jump
  as soon as they open the net.

01:23:44.986 --> 01:23:48.956
-[ Pippi ] Tell the Glue Man
 to jump first.
-Glue Man? What's a Glue Man?

01:23:49.023 --> 01:23:52.793
My friend up there.
Gregory, you'll have
to jump first.

01:23:52.860 --> 01:23:56.130
Don't worry.
I'll save them.

01:23:56.197 --> 01:23:59.900
- <i>Now, it's perfectly safe.</i>
- He's gonna jump.

01:23:59.967 --> 01:24:04.205
- It's all right.
  I'll get them down!
- <i>[ Billy ] Help! Help!</i>

01:24:04.271 --> 01:24:07.608
It's much easier
than walking down a wall.
                    What wall?

01:24:07.675 --> 01:24:10.878
                You got a rope?
Yeah. Right there
in the back.

01:24:10.945 --> 01:24:14.048
Don't worry!
It's all right!
I'll get them out!

01:24:14.115 --> 01:24:17.251
Bravo, Gregory!
Hi, Tommy and Annika.

01:24:17.318 --> 01:24:21.055
    Oh, Pippi, I'm so glad
    you're okay.
We came to rescue you.

01:24:21.122 --> 01:24:25.793
You'll be safe.
Whoa-oa-oa!

01:24:25.860 --> 01:24:29.563
<i>[ Chattering, Shouting</i>
<i>  Continue ]</i>

01:24:29.630 --> 01:24:32.566
- Come on!
  Don't be afraid! Jump!
- Help!

01:24:32.633 --> 01:24:37.538
It's Chrissy and Billy!
Mr. Neilson, you're
exactly what I need.

01:24:37.605 --> 01:24:41.409
You've gotta jump!
Close your eyes and jump!

01:24:41.475 --> 01:24:43.811
<i>The boy first!</i>

01:24:43.878 --> 01:24:47.481
   [ Chattering Continues ]
<i>Now, listen, kid:</i>

01:24:47.548 --> 01:24:51.152
<i>Close your eyes and jump.</i>
   [ Mr. Neilson Chittering ]

01:24:54.021 --> 01:24:57.992
- [ Both Screaming ]
- Come on! Come on!
  It's fun!

01:24:58.059 --> 01:25:03.064
<i>I did it,</i>
<i>and I'm all right!</i>
<i>[ Billy ] Pippi! Help!</i>

01:25:03.130 --> 01:25:06.167
- <i>Pippi! Pippi!</i>
- <i>[ Mrs. Settigren ]</i>
 <i>What's she doing?</i>

01:25:06.233 --> 01:25:12.239
Now, you're gonna take this rope
over there. Just jump.
It's not gonna hurt you.

01:25:12.306 --> 01:25:15.476
- <i>[ People Gasping ]</i>
- <i>Get some water on that cable!</i>
- Well done, Mr. Neilson.

01:25:15.543 --> 01:25:19.113
- <i>Tie the rope to something.</i>
- <i>[ Firefighter ]</i>
 <i>  We need more pressure.</i>

01:25:19.180 --> 01:25:24.085
<i>[ Billy ]</i>
<i>Help! Pippi! Save us!</i>
<i>We're gonna burn!</i>

01:25:24.151 --> 01:25:27.288
                     <i>Help!</i>
Don't worry.
I'm coming for you.

01:25:27.354 --> 01:25:29.957
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Careful. Careful.</i>

01:25:30.024 --> 01:25:32.560
Come on, Pippi!
You can do it!

01:25:32.626 --> 01:25:35.963
[ Kids ]
Help! Hurry!
[ Screaming ]

01:25:36.030 --> 01:25:41.001
Hold on, Billy, Chrissy.
 <i>[ Annika ]</i>
 <i>Be careful, Pippi!</i>

01:25:41.068 --> 01:25:45.573
<i>[ Firefighter ] Careful.</i>
<i>[ Chrissy ]</i>
<i>Pippi! Help!</i>

01:25:45.639 --> 01:25:50.544
         <i>Pippi, it's hot!</i>
         <i>Help!</i>
I'm coming.

01:25:50.611 --> 01:25:53.380
You're doing it!
 You're doing it!

01:25:53.447 --> 01:25:56.951
        <i>[ Billy ]</i>
        <i>Help! Help, Pippi!</i>
<i>Well done!</i>

01:25:57.017 --> 01:26:01.555
She did it!
 She did it! She did--

01:26:01.622 --> 01:26:04.225
Uh-oh.

01:26:04.291 --> 01:26:06.460
Put your head
under my arm.
Okay. There.

01:26:06.527 --> 01:26:09.296
Let them jump.
We'll catch them.
    [ All ] No.

01:26:09.363 --> 01:26:12.333
Here we go.

01:26:12.399 --> 01:26:15.002
What's she trying to do?
She'll never make it.

01:26:21.842 --> 01:26:24.612
- [ Gasping ]
- [ Chrissy Whimpering ]

01:26:24.678 --> 01:26:26.247
You okay?
        Uh-huh.

01:26:28.149 --> 01:26:31.051
[ Chrissy
  Continues Whimpering ]

01:26:35.723 --> 01:26:39.927
- <i>[ All Cheering ]</i>
- Three cheers for Pippi!

01:26:42.630 --> 01:26:45.166
<i>[ Pippi ]</i>
<i>Careful. Mr. Neilson,</i>
<i>where are you?</i>

01:26:45.232 --> 01:26:50.771
Mr. Neilson, come over.
Run along the ropes.
You're a monkey, aren't you?

01:26:53.841 --> 01:26:56.677
Mr. Neilson,
I don't want roast monkey
for dinner.

01:26:56.744 --> 01:27:00.347
- [ Chittering ]
- <i>Come on. Right now.</i>
 <i>Stop fooling around.</i>

01:27:00.414 --> 01:27:03.617
- [ Continues Chittering ]
- Very well.

01:27:09.757 --> 01:27:12.726
[ Chittering ]

01:27:18.933 --> 01:27:22.870
- [ Cheering ]
- Come on, you silly boy.
  Okay?

01:27:33.647 --> 01:27:36.083
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>
<i>The rope!</i>
<i>It's starting to burn!</i>

01:27:40.154 --> 01:27:43.824
- Ow! You're hurting me!
  [ Screams ]
- [ All Gasping ]

01:27:43.891 --> 01:27:48.729
<i>[ People Screaming ]</i>
   [ Mr. Neilson Chittering ]

01:27:48.796 --> 01:27:54.568
- [ All Cheering ]
- Mr. Neilson, you're
  the best monkey in the world.

01:27:54.635 --> 01:27:59.106
- I'm so proud of you!
  You were terrific!
- You were great!

01:27:59.173 --> 01:28:02.743
Oh, I'm afraid
I misjudged you.

01:28:02.810 --> 01:28:07.581
- How can I make it up to you?
- I'd really like to go back
  to Villa Villekulla.

01:28:07.648 --> 01:28:11.085
Mr. Neilson and Alfonso
must be pretty mad at me.

01:28:12.620 --> 01:28:14.421
Oh, Pippi.

01:28:18.325 --> 01:28:23.697
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i> In my mind I hear your voice</i>
<i>  is callin' </i>

01:28:23.764 --> 01:28:27.468
<i>Come on</i>
<i> Be happy somehow</i>

01:28:27.534 --> 01:28:33.107
[ Pippi Singing Along ]
 Deck the halls
  with lots of holly

01:28:33.173 --> 01:28:38.345
     Shine your lights
      for the world to see
[ Chittering ]

